56UseMipsTailCalls("mips-tail-calls", cl::Hidden,

59static cl::opt<bool> NoDPLoadStore("mno-ldc1-sdc1", cl::init(false),

64MipsSETargetLowering::MipsSETargetLowering(const MipsTargetMachine &TM,
65 const MipsSubtarget &STI)
66 : MipsTargetLowering(TM, STI) {
67 // Set up the register classes
68 addRegisterClass(MVT::i32, &Mips::GPR32RegClass);
69
70 if (Subtarget.isGP64bit())
71 addRegisterClass(MVT::i64, &Mips::GPR64RegClass);
72
73 if (Subtarget.hasDSP() || Subtarget.hasMSA()) {
74 // Expand all truncating stores and extending loads.
75 for (MVT VT0 : MVT::vector_valuetypes()) {
76 for (MVT VT1 : MVT::vector_valuetypes()) {
77 setTruncStoreAction(VT0, VT1, Expand);
78 setLoadExtAction(ISD::SEXTLOAD, VT0, VT1, Expand);
79 setLoadExtAction(ISD::ZEXTLOAD, VT0, VT1, Expand);
80 setLoadExtAction(ISD::EXTLOAD, VT0, VT1, Expand);
81 }
82 }
83 }
84
85 if (Subtarget.hasDSP()) {
86 MVT::SimpleValueType VecTys[2] = {MVT::v2i16, MVT::v4i8};
87
88 for (unsigned i = 0; i < array_lengthof(VecTys); ++i) {
89 addRegisterClass(VecTys[i], &Mips::DSPRRegClass);
90
91 // Expand all builtin opcodes.
92 for (unsigned Opc = 0; Opc < ISD::BUILTIN_OP_END; ++Opc)
93 setOperationAction(Opc, VecTys[i], Expand);
94
95 setOperationAction(ISD::ADD, VecTys[i], Legal);
96 setOperationAction(ISD::SUB, VecTys[i], Legal);
97 setOperationAction(ISD::LOAD, VecTys[i], Legal);
98 setOperationAction(ISD::STORE, VecTys[i], Legal);
99 setOperationAction(ISD::BITCAST, VecTys[i], Legal);
100 }
101
102 setTargetDAGCombine(ISD::SHL);
103 setTargetDAGCombine(ISD::SRA);
104 setTargetDAGCombine(ISD::SRL);
105 setTargetDAGCombine(ISD::SETCC);
106 setTargetDAGCombine(ISD::VSELECT);
107
108 if (Subtarget.hasMips32r2()) {
109 setOperationAction(ISD::ADDC, MVT::i32, Legal);
110 setOperationAction(ISD::ADDE, MVT::i32, Legal);
111 }
112 }
113
114 if (Subtarget.hasDSPR2())
115 setOperationAction(ISD::MUL, MVT::v2i16, Legal);
116
117 if (Subtarget.hasMSA()) {
118 addMSAIntType(MVT::v16i8, &Mips::MSA128BRegClass);
119 addMSAIntType(MVT::v8i16, &Mips::MSA128HRegClass);
120 addMSAIntType(MVT::v4i32, &Mips::MSA128WRegClass);
121 addMSAIntType(MVT::v2i64, &Mips::MSA128DRegClass);
122 addMSAFloatType(MVT::v8f16, &Mips::MSA128HRegClass);
123 addMSAFloatType(MVT::v4f32, &Mips::MSA128WRegClass);
124 addMSAFloatType(MVT::v2f64, &Mips::MSA128DRegClass);
125
126 // f16 is a storage-only type, always promote it to f32.
127 addRegisterClass(MVT::f16, &Mips::MSA128HRegClass);
128 setOperationAction(ISD::SETCC, MVT::f16, Promote);
129 setOperationAction(ISD::BR_CC, MVT::f16, Promote);
130 setOperationAction(ISD::SELECT_CC, MVT::f16, Promote);
131 setOperationAction(ISD::SELECT, MVT::f16, Promote);
132 setOperationAction(ISD::FADD, MVT::f16, Promote);
133 setOperationAction(ISD::FSUB, MVT::f16, Promote);
134 setOperationAction(ISD::FMUL, MVT::f16, Promote);
135 setOperationAction(ISD::FDIV, MVT::f16, Promote);
136 setOperationAction(ISD::FREM, MVT::f16, Promote);
137 setOperationAction(ISD::FMA, MVT::f16, Promote);
138 setOperationAction(ISD::FNEG, MVT::f16, Promote);
139 setOperationAction(ISD::FABS, MVT::f16, Promote);
140 setOperationAction(ISD::FCEIL, MVT::f16, Promote);
141 setOperationAction(ISD::FCOPYSIGN, MVT::f16, Promote);
142 setOperationAction(ISD::FCOS, MVT::f16, Promote);
143 setOperationAction(ISD::FP_EXTEND, MVT::f16, Promote);
144 setOperationAction(ISD::FFLOOR, MVT::f16, Promote);
145 setOperationAction(ISD::FNEARBYINT, MVT::f16, Promote);
146 setOperationAction(ISD::FPOW, MVT::f16, Promote);
147 setOperationAction(ISD::FPOWI, MVT::f16, Promote);
148 setOperationAction(ISD::FRINT, MVT::f16, Promote);
149 setOperationAction(ISD::FSIN, MVT::f16, Promote);
150 setOperationAction(ISD::FSINCOS, MVT::f16, Promote);
151 setOperationAction(ISD::FSQRT, MVT::f16, Promote);
152 setOperationAction(ISD::FEXP, MVT::f16, Promote);
153 setOperationAction(ISD::FEXP2, MVT::f16, Promote);
154 setOperationAction(ISD::FLOG, MVT::f16, Promote);
155 setOperationAction(ISD::FLOG2, MVT::f16, Promote);
156 setOperationAction(ISD::FLOG10, MVT::f16, Promote);
157 setOperationAction(ISD::FROUND, MVT::f16, Promote);
158 setOperationAction(ISD::FTRUNC, MVT::f16, Promote);
159 setOperationAction(ISD::FMINNUM, MVT::f16, Promote);
160 setOperationAction(ISD::FMAXNUM, MVT::f16, Promote);
161 setOperationAction(ISD::FMINIMUM, MVT::f16, Promote);
162 setOperationAction(ISD::FMAXIMUM, MVT::f16, Promote);
163
164 setTargetDAGCombine(ISD::AND);
165 setTargetDAGCombine(ISD::OR);
166 setTargetDAGCombine(ISD::SRA);
167 setTargetDAGCombine(ISD::VSELECT);
168 setTargetDAGCombine(ISD::XOR);
169 }
170
171 if (!Subtarget.useSoftFloat()) {
172 addRegisterClass(MVT::f32, &Mips::FGR32RegClass);
173
174 // When dealing with single precision only, use libcalls
175 if (!Subtarget.isSingleFloat()) {
176 if (Subtarget.isFP64bit())
177 addRegisterClass(MVT::f64, &Mips::FGR64RegClass);
178 else
179 addRegisterClass(MVT::f64, &Mips::AFGR64RegClass);
180 }
181 }
182
183 if (Subtarget.isCheri()) {
184 // This crashes: addRegisterClass(CapType, &Mips::CheriRegsAllRegClass);
185 addRegisterClass(CapType, &Mips::CheriGPRRegClass);
186 setTruncStoreAction(MVT::i32, MVT::i8, Custom);
187 setTruncStoreAction(MVT::i32, MVT::i16, Custom);
188 setLoadExtAction(ISD::EXTLOAD, MVT::i8, MVT::i32, Custom);
189 setLoadExtAction(ISD::SEXTLOAD, MVT::i8, MVT::i32, Custom);
190 setLoadExtAction(ISD::ZEXTLOAD, MVT::i8, MVT::i32, Custom);
191 setLoadExtAction(ISD::EXTLOAD, MVT::i16, MVT::i32, Custom);
192 setLoadExtAction(ISD::SEXTLOAD, MVT::i16, MVT::i32, Custom);
193 setLoadExtAction(ISD::ZEXTLOAD, MVT::i16, MVT::i32, Custom);
194 setLoadExtAction(ISD::EXTLOAD, MVT::i8, MVT::i64, Custom);
195 setLoadExtAction(ISD::SEXTLOAD, MVT::i8, MVT::i64, Custom);
196 setLoadExtAction(ISD::ZEXTLOAD, MVT::i8, MVT::i64, Custom);
197 setLoadExtAction(ISD::EXTLOAD, MVT::i16, MVT::i64, Custom);
198 setLoadExtAction(ISD::SEXTLOAD, MVT::i16, MVT::i64, Custom);
199 setLoadExtAction(ISD::ZEXTLOAD, MVT::i16, MVT::i64, Custom);
200 setOperationAction(ISD::SETCC, CapType, Legal);
201 setOperationAction(ISD::SELECT, CapType, Legal);
202 setOperationAction(ISD::SELECT_CC, CapType, Expand);
203 setOperationAction(ISD::BR_CC, CapType, Expand);
204 } else
205 addRegisterClass(CapType, &Mips::FakeCheriRegsRegClass);
206
207 setOperationAction(ISD::SMUL_LOHI, MVT::i32, Custom);
208 setOperationAction(ISD::UMUL_LOHI, MVT::i32, Custom);
209 setOperationAction(ISD::MULHS, MVT::i32, Custom);
210 setOperationAction(ISD::MULHU, MVT::i32, Custom);
211
212 if (Subtarget.hasCnMips())
213 setOperationAction(ISD::MUL, MVT::i64, Legal);
214 else if (Subtarget.isGP64bit())
215 setOperationAction(ISD::MUL, MVT::i64, Custom);
216
217 if (Subtarget.isGP64bit()) {
218 setOperationAction(ISD::SMUL_LOHI, MVT::i64, Custom);
219 setOperationAction(ISD::UMUL_LOHI, MVT::i64, Custom);
220 setOperationAction(ISD::MULHS, MVT::i64, Custom);
221 setOperationAction(ISD::MULHU, MVT::i64, Custom);
222 setOperationAction(ISD::SDIVREM, MVT::i64, Custom);
223 setOperationAction(ISD::UDIVREM, MVT::i64, Custom);
224 }
225
226 setOperationAction(ISD::INTRINSIC_WO_CHAIN, MVT::i64, Custom);
227 setOperationAction(ISD::INTRINSIC_W_CHAIN, MVT::i64, Custom);
228
229 setOperationAction(ISD::SDIVREM, MVT::i32, Custom);
230 setOperationAction(ISD::UDIVREM, MVT::i32, Custom);
231 setOperationAction(ISD::ATOMIC_FENCE, MVT::Other, Custom);
232 setOperationAction(ISD::LOAD, MVT::i32, Custom);
233 setOperationAction(ISD::STORE, MVT::i32, Custom);
234
235 setTargetDAGCombine(ISD::MUL);
236
237 setOperationAction(ISD::INTRINSIC_WO_CHAIN, MVT::Other, Custom);
238 setOperationAction(ISD::INTRINSIC_W_CHAIN, MVT::Other, Custom);
239 setOperationAction(ISD::INTRINSIC_VOID, MVT::Other, Custom);
240
241 if (Subtarget.hasMips32r2() && !Subtarget.useSoftFloat() &&
242 !Subtarget.hasMips64()) {
243 setOperationAction(ISD::BITCAST, MVT::i64, Custom);
244 }
245
246 if (NoDPLoadStore) {
247 setOperationAction(ISD::LOAD, MVT::f64, Custom);
248 setOperationAction(ISD::STORE, MVT::f64, Custom);
249 }
250
251 if (Subtarget.hasMips32r6()) {
252 // MIPS32r6 replaces the accumulator-based multiplies with a three register
253 // instruction
254 setOperationAction(ISD::SMUL_LOHI, MVT::i32, Expand);
255 setOperationAction(ISD::UMUL_LOHI, MVT::i32, Expand);
256 setOperationAction(ISD::MUL, MVT::i32, Legal);
257 setOperationAction(ISD::MULHS, MVT::i32, Legal);
258 setOperationAction(ISD::MULHU, MVT::i32, Legal);
259
260 // MIPS32r6 replaces the accumulator-based division/remainder with separate
261 // three register division and remainder instructions.
262 setOperationAction(ISD::SDIVREM, MVT::i32, Expand);
263 setOperationAction(ISD::UDIVREM, MVT::i32, Expand);
264 setOperationAction(ISD::SDIV, MVT::i32, Legal);
265 setOperationAction(ISD::UDIV, MVT::i32, Legal);
266 setOperationAction(ISD::SREM, MVT::i32, Legal);
267 setOperationAction(ISD::UREM, MVT::i32, Legal);
268
269 // MIPS32r6 replaces conditional moves with an equivalent that removes the
270 // need for three GPR read ports.
271 setOperationAction(ISD::SETCC, MVT::i32, Legal);
272 setOperationAction(ISD::SELECT, MVT::i32, Legal);
273 setOperationAction(ISD::SELECT_CC, MVT::i32, Expand);
274
275 setOperationAction(ISD::SETCC, MVT::f32, Legal);
276 setOperationAction(ISD::SELECT, MVT::f32, Legal);
277 setOperationAction(ISD::SELECT_CC, MVT::f32, Expand);
278
279 assert(Subtarget.isFP64bit() && "FR=1 is required for MIPS32r6");
280 setOperationAction(ISD::SETCC, MVT::f64, Legal);
281 setOperationAction(ISD::SELECT, MVT::f64, Custom);
282 setOperationAction(ISD::SELECT_CC, MVT::f64, Expand);
283
284 setOperationAction(ISD::BRCOND, MVT::Other, Legal);
285
286 // Floating point > and >= are supported via < and <=
287 setCondCodeAction(ISD::SETOGE, MVT::f32, Expand);
288 setCondCodeAction(ISD::SETOGT, MVT::f32, Expand);
289 setCondCodeAction(ISD::SETUGE, MVT::f32, Expand);
290 setCondCodeAction(ISD::SETUGT, MVT::f32, Expand);
291
292 setCondCodeAction(ISD::SETOGE, MVT::f64, Expand);
293 setCondCodeAction(ISD::SETOGT, MVT::f64, Expand);
294 setCondCodeAction(ISD::SETUGE, MVT::f64, Expand);
295 setCondCodeAction(ISD::SETUGT, MVT::f64, Expand);
296 }
297
298 if (Subtarget.hasMips64r6()) {
299 // FIXME: we should really do some smarter expanding
300 // MIPS64r6 replaces the accumulator-based multiplies with a three register
301 // instruction
302 setOperationAction(ISD::SMUL_LOHI, MVT::i64, Expand);
303 setOperationAction(ISD::UMUL_LOHI, MVT::i64, Expand);
304 setOperationAction(ISD::MUL, MVT::i64, Legal);
305 setOperationAction(ISD::MULHS, MVT::i64, Legal);
306 setOperationAction(ISD::MULHU, MVT::i64, Legal);
307
308 // MIPS32r6 replaces the accumulator-based division/remainder with separate
309 // three register division and remainder instructions.
310 setOperationAction(ISD::SDIVREM, MVT::i64, Expand);
311 setOperationAction(ISD::UDIVREM, MVT::i64, Expand);
312 setOperationAction(ISD::SDIV, MVT::i64, Legal);
313 setOperationAction(ISD::UDIV, MVT::i64, Legal);
314 setOperationAction(ISD::SREM, MVT::i64, Legal);
315 setOperationAction(ISD::UREM, MVT::i64, Legal);
316
317 // MIPS64r6 replaces conditional moves with an equivalent that removes the
318 // need for three GPR read ports.
319 setOperationAction(ISD::SETCC, MVT::i64, Legal);
320 setOperationAction(ISD::SELECT, MVT::i64, Legal);
321 setOperationAction(ISD::SELECT_CC, MVT::i64, Expand);
322 }
323
324 computeRegisterProperties(Subtarget.getRegisterInfo());
325}

334 return Subtarget.isABI_CheriPureCap() ? 200 : 0;
335}

337const TargetRegisterClass *
338MipsSETargetLowering::getRepRegClassFor(MVT VT) const {
339 if (VT == MVT::Untyped)
340 return Subtarget.hasDSP() ? &Mips::ACC64DSPRegClass : &Mips::ACC64RegClass;
341
342 return TargetLowering::getRepRegClassFor(VT);
343}

345// Enable MSA support for the given integer type and Register class.
346void MipsSETargetLowering::
347addMSAIntType(MVT::SimpleValueType Ty, const TargetRegisterClass *RC) {
348 addRegisterClass(Ty, RC);
349
350 // Expand all builtin opcodes.
351 for (unsigned Opc = 0; Opc < ISD::BUILTIN_OP_END; ++Opc)
352 setOperationAction(Opc, Ty, Expand);
353
354 setOperationAction(ISD::BITCAST, Ty, Legal);
355 setOperationAction(ISD::LOAD, Ty, Legal);
356 setOperationAction(ISD::STORE, Ty, Legal);
357 setOperationAction(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, Ty, Custom);
358 setOperationAction(ISD::INSERT_VECTOR_ELT, Ty, Legal);
359 setOperationAction(ISD::BUILD_VECTOR, Ty, Custom);
360
361 setOperationAction(ISD::ADD, Ty, Legal);
362 setOperationAction(ISD::AND, Ty, Legal);
363 setOperationAction(ISD::CTLZ, Ty, Legal);
364 setOperationAction(ISD::CTPOP, Ty, Legal);
365 setOperationAction(ISD::MUL, Ty, Legal);
366 setOperationAction(ISD::OR, Ty, Legal);
367 setOperationAction(ISD::SDIV, Ty, Legal);
368 setOperationAction(ISD::SREM, Ty, Legal);
369 setOperationAction(ISD::SHL, Ty, Legal);
370 setOperationAction(ISD::SRA, Ty, Legal);
371 setOperationAction(ISD::SRL, Ty, Legal);
372 setOperationAction(ISD::SUB, Ty, Legal);
373 setOperationAction(ISD::SMAX, Ty, Legal);
374 setOperationAction(ISD::SMIN, Ty, Legal);
375 setOperationAction(ISD::UDIV, Ty, Legal);
376 setOperationAction(ISD::UREM, Ty, Legal);
377 setOperationAction(ISD::UMAX, Ty, Legal);
378 setOperationAction(ISD::UMIN, Ty, Legal);
379 setOperationAction(ISD::VECTOR_SHUFFLE, Ty, Custom);
380 setOperationAction(ISD::VSELECT, Ty, Legal);
381 setOperationAction(ISD::XOR, Ty, Legal);
382
383 if (Ty == MVT::v4i32 || Ty == MVT::v2i64) {
384 setOperationAction(ISD::FP_TO_SINT, Ty, Legal);
385 setOperationAction(ISD::FP_TO_UINT, Ty, Legal);
386 setOperationAction(ISD::SINT_TO_FP, Ty, Legal);
387 setOperationAction(ISD::UINT_TO_FP, Ty, Legal);
388 }
389
390 setOperationAction(ISD::SETCC, Ty, Legal);
391 setCondCodeAction(ISD::SETNE, Ty, Expand);
392 setCondCodeAction(ISD::SETGE, Ty, Expand);
393 setCondCodeAction(ISD::SETGT, Ty, Expand);
394 setCondCodeAction(ISD::SETUGE, Ty, Expand);
395 setCondCodeAction(ISD::SETUGT, Ty, Expand);
396}

398// Enable MSA support for the given floating-point type and Register class.
399void MipsSETargetLowering::
400addMSAFloatType(MVT::SimpleValueType Ty, const TargetRegisterClass *RC) {
401 addRegisterClass(Ty, RC);
402
403 // Expand all builtin opcodes.
404 for (unsigned Opc = 0; Opc < ISD::BUILTIN_OP_END; ++Opc)
405 setOperationAction(Opc, Ty, Expand);
406
407 setOperationAction(ISD::LOAD, Ty, Legal);
408 setOperationAction(ISD::STORE, Ty, Legal);
409 setOperationAction(ISD::BITCAST, Ty, Legal);
410 setOperationAction(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, Ty, Legal);
411 setOperationAction(ISD::INSERT_VECTOR_ELT, Ty, Legal);
412 setOperationAction(ISD::BUILD_VECTOR, Ty, Custom);
413
414 if (Ty != MVT::v8f16) {
415 setOperationAction(ISD::FABS, Ty, Legal);
416 setOperationAction(ISD::FADD, Ty, Legal);
417 setOperationAction(ISD::FDIV, Ty, Legal);
418 setOperationAction(ISD::FEXP2, Ty, Legal);
419 setOperationAction(ISD::FLOG2, Ty, Legal);
420 setOperationAction(ISD::FMA, Ty, Legal);
421 setOperationAction(ISD::FMUL, Ty, Legal);
422 setOperationAction(ISD::FRINT, Ty, Legal);
423 setOperationAction(ISD::FSQRT, Ty, Legal);
424 setOperationAction(ISD::FSUB, Ty, Legal);
425 setOperationAction(ISD::VSELECT, Ty, Legal);
426
427 setOperationAction(ISD::SETCC, Ty, Legal);
428 setCondCodeAction(ISD::SETOGE, Ty, Expand);
429 setCondCodeAction(ISD::SETOGT, Ty, Expand);
430 setCondCodeAction(ISD::SETUGE, Ty, Expand);
431 setCondCodeAction(ISD::SETUGT, Ty, Expand);
432 setCondCodeAction(ISD::SETGE, Ty, Expand);
433 setCondCodeAction(ISD::SETGT, Ty, Expand);
434 }

436
437SDValue MipsSETargetLowering::lowerSELECT(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
438 if(!Subtarget.hasMips32r6())
439 return MipsTargetLowering::LowerOperation(Op, DAG);
440
441 EVT ResTy = Op->getValueType(0);
442 SDLoc DL(Op);
443
444 // Although MTC1_D64 takes an i32 and writes an f64, the upper 32 bits of the
445 // floating point register are undefined. Not really an issue as sel.d, which
446 // is produced from an FSELECT node, only looks at bit 0.
447 SDValue Tmp = DAG.getNode(MipsISD::MTC1_D64, DL, MVT::f64, Op->getOperand(0));
448 return DAG.getNode(MipsISD::FSELECT, DL, ResTy, Tmp, Op->getOperand(1),
449 Op->getOperand(2));
450}
451
452bool MipsSETargetLowering::allowsMisalignedMemoryAccesses(
453 EVT VT, unsigned AS, unsigned, MachineMemOperand::Flags, bool *Fast) const {
454 // capabilities must be aligned
455 if (VT.isFatPointer())
456 return false;
457
458 MVT::SimpleValueType SVT = VT.getSimpleVT().SimpleTy;
459
460 if (Subtarget.systemSupportsUnalignedAccess(AS)) {
461 // MIPS32r6/MIPS64r6 is required to support unaligned access. It's
462 // implementation defined whether this is handled by hardware, software, or
463 // a hybrid of the two but it's expected that most implementations will
464 // handle the majority of cases in hardware.
465 if (Fast) {
466 // CHERI used to support unaligned loads and stores within a cache-line
467 // but now it is emulated in the OS instead.
468 if (Subtarget.isCheri())
469 *Fast = false;
470 else
471 *Fast = true;
472 }
473 return true;
474 }
475
476 switch (SVT) {
477 case MVT::i64: // LDL/LDR/SDL/SDR
478 case MVT::i32: // LWL/LWR/SWL/SWR
479 if (Fast)
480 *Fast = true;
481 return AS == 0;
482 default:
483 return false;
484 }
485}
486
487SDValue MipsSETargetLowering::LowerOperation(SDValue Op,
488 SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
489 switch(Op.getOpcode()) {
490 case ISD::LOAD: return lowerLOAD(Op, DAG);
491 case ISD::STORE: return lowerSTORE(Op, DAG);
492 case ISD::SMUL_LOHI: return lowerMulDiv(Op, MipsISD::Mult, true, true, DAG);
493 case ISD::UMUL_LOHI: return lowerMulDiv(Op, MipsISD::Multu, true, true, DAG);
494 case ISD::MULHS: return lowerMulDiv(Op, MipsISD::Mult, false, true, DAG);
495 case ISD::MULHU: return lowerMulDiv(Op, MipsISD::Multu, false, true, DAG);
496 case ISD::MUL: return lowerMulDiv(Op, MipsISD::Mult, true, false, DAG);
497 case ISD::SDIVREM: return lowerMulDiv(Op, MipsISD::DivRem, true, true, DAG);
498 case ISD::UDIVREM: return lowerMulDiv(Op, MipsISD::DivRemU, true, true,
499 DAG);
500 case ISD::INTRINSIC_WO_CHAIN: return lowerINTRINSIC_WO_CHAIN(Op, DAG);
501 case ISD::INTRINSIC_W_CHAIN: return lowerINTRINSIC_W_CHAIN(Op, DAG);
502 case ISD::INTRINSIC_VOID: return lowerINTRINSIC_VOID(Op, DAG);
503 case ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT: return lowerEXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT(Op, DAG);
504 case ISD::BUILD_VECTOR: return lowerBUILD_VECTOR(Op, DAG);
505 case ISD::VECTOR_SHUFFLE: return lowerVECTOR_SHUFFLE(Op, DAG);
506 case ISD::SELECT: return lowerSELECT(Op, DAG);
507 case ISD::BITCAST: return lowerBITCAST(Op, DAG);
508 }
509
510 return MipsTargetLowering::LowerOperation(Op, DAG);
511}
512
513// Fold zero extensions into MipsISD::VEXTRACT_[SZ]EXT_ELT
514//
515// Performs the following transformations:
516// - Changes MipsISD::VEXTRACT_[SZ]EXT_ELT to zero extension if its
517// sign/zero-extension is completely overwritten by the new one performed by
518// the ISD::AND.
519// - Removes redundant zero extensions performed by an ISD::AND.
520static SDValue performANDCombine(SDNode *N, SelectionDAG &DAG,
521 TargetLowering::DAGCombinerInfo &DCI,
522 const MipsSubtarget &Subtarget) {
523 if (!Subtarget.hasMSA())
524 return SDValue();
525
526 SDValue Op0 = N->getOperand(0);
527 SDValue Op1 = N->getOperand(1);
528 unsigned Op0Opcode = Op0->getOpcode();
529
530 // (and (MipsVExtract[SZ]Ext $a, $b, $c), imm:$d)
531 // where $d + 1 == 2^n and n == 32
532 // or $d + 1 == 2^n and n <= 32 and ZExt
533 // -> (MipsVExtractZExt $a, $b, $c)
534 if (Op0Opcode == MipsISD::VEXTRACT_SEXT_ELT ||
535 Op0Opcode == MipsISD::VEXTRACT_ZEXT_ELT) {
536 ConstantSDNode *Mask = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op1);
537
538 if (!Mask)
539 return SDValue();
540
541 int32_t Log2IfPositive = (Mask->getAPIntValue() + 1).exactLogBase2();
542
543 if (Log2IfPositive <= 0)
544 return SDValue(); // Mask+1 is not a power of 2
545
546 SDValue Op0Op2 = Op0->getOperand(2);
547 EVT ExtendTy = cast<VTSDNode>(Op0Op2)->getVT();
548 unsigned ExtendTySize = ExtendTy.getSizeInBits();
549 unsigned Log2 = Log2IfPositive;
550
551 if ((Op0Opcode == MipsISD::VEXTRACT_ZEXT_ELT && Log2 >= ExtendTySize) ||
552 Log2 == ExtendTySize) {
553 SDValue Ops[] = { Op0->getOperand(0), Op0->getOperand(1), Op0Op2 };
554 return DAG.getNode(MipsISD::VEXTRACT_ZEXT_ELT, SDLoc(Op0),
555 Op0->getVTList(),
556 makeArrayRef(Ops, Op0->getNumOperands()));
557 }
558 }
559
560 return SDValue();
561}
562
563// Determine if the specified node is a constant vector splat.
564//
565// Returns true and sets Imm if:
566// * N is a ISD::BUILD_VECTOR representing a constant splat
567//
568// This function is quite similar to MipsSEDAGToDAGISel::selectVSplat. The
569// differences are that it assumes the MSA has already been checked and the
570// arbitrary requirement for a maximum of 32-bit integers isn't applied (and
571// must not be in order for binsri.d to be selectable).
572static bool isVSplat(SDValue N, APInt &Imm, bool IsLittleEndian) {
573 BuildVectorSDNode *Node = dyn_cast<BuildVectorSDNode>(N.getNode());
574
575 if (!Node)
576 return false;
577
578 APInt SplatValue, SplatUndef;
579 unsigned SplatBitSize;
580 bool HasAnyUndefs;
581
582 if (!Node->isConstantSplat(SplatValue, SplatUndef, SplatBitSize, HasAnyUndefs,
583 8, !IsLittleEndian))
584 return false;
585
586 Imm = SplatValue;
587
588 return true;
589}
590
591// Test whether the given node is an all-ones build_vector.
592static bool isVectorAllOnes(SDValue N) {
593 // Look through bitcasts. Endianness doesn't matter because we are looking
594 // for an all-ones value.
595 if (N->getOpcode() == ISD::BITCAST)
596 N = N->getOperand(0);
597
598 BuildVectorSDNode *BVN = dyn_cast<BuildVectorSDNode>(N);
599
600 if (!BVN)
601 return false;
602
603 APInt SplatValue, SplatUndef;
604 unsigned SplatBitSize;
605 bool HasAnyUndefs;
606
607 // Endianness doesn't matter in this context because we are looking for
608 // an all-ones value.
609 if (BVN->isConstantSplat(SplatValue, SplatUndef, SplatBitSize, HasAnyUndefs))
610 return SplatValue.isAllOnesValue();
611
612 return false;
613}
614
615// Test whether N is the bitwise inverse of OfNode.
616static bool isBitwiseInverse(SDValue N, SDValue OfNode) {
617 if (N->getOpcode() != ISD::XOR)
618 return false;
619
620 if (isVectorAllOnes(N->getOperand(0)))
621 return N->getOperand(1) == OfNode;
622
623 if (isVectorAllOnes(N->getOperand(1)))
624 return N->getOperand(0) == OfNode;
625
626 return false;
627}
628
629// Perform combines where ISD::OR is the root node.
630//
631// Performs the following transformations:
632// - (or (and $a, $mask), (and $b, $inv_mask)) => (vselect $mask, $a, $b)
633// where $inv_mask is the bitwise inverse of $mask and the 'or' has a 128-bit
634// vector type.
635static SDValue performORCombine(SDNode *N, SelectionDAG &DAG,
636 TargetLowering::DAGCombinerInfo &DCI,
637 const MipsSubtarget &Subtarget) {
638 if (!Subtarget.hasMSA())
639 return SDValue();
640
641 EVT Ty = N->getValueType(0);
642
643 if (!Ty.is128BitVector())
644 return SDValue();
645
646 SDValue Op0 = N->getOperand(0);
647 SDValue Op1 = N->getOperand(1);
648
649 if (Op0->getOpcode() == ISD::AND && Op1->getOpcode() == ISD::AND) {
650 SDValue Op0Op0 = Op0->getOperand(0);
651 SDValue Op0Op1 = Op0->getOperand(1);
652 SDValue Op1Op0 = Op1->getOperand(0);
653 SDValue Op1Op1 = Op1->getOperand(1);
654 bool IsLittleEndian = !Subtarget.isLittle();
655
656 SDValue IfSet, IfClr, Cond;
657 bool IsConstantMask = false;
658 APInt Mask, InvMask;
659
660 // If Op0Op0 is an appropriate mask, try to find it's inverse in either
661 // Op1Op0, or Op1Op1. Keep track of the Cond, IfSet, and IfClr nodes, while
662 // looking.
663 // IfClr will be set if we find a valid match.
664 if (isVSplat(Op0Op0, Mask, IsLittleEndian)) {
665 Cond = Op0Op0;
666 IfSet = Op0Op1;
667
668 if (isVSplat(Op1Op0, InvMask, IsLittleEndian) &&
669 Mask.getBitWidth() == InvMask.getBitWidth() && Mask == ~InvMask)
670 IfClr = Op1Op1;
671 else if (isVSplat(Op1Op1, InvMask, IsLittleEndian) &&
672 Mask.getBitWidth() == InvMask.getBitWidth() && Mask == ~InvMask)
673 IfClr = Op1Op0;
674
675 IsConstantMask = true;
676 }
677
678 // If IfClr is not yet set, and Op0Op1 is an appropriate mask, try the same
679 // thing again using this mask.
680 // IfClr will be set if we find a valid match.
681 if (!IfClr.getNode() && isVSplat(Op0Op1, Mask, IsLittleEndian)) {
682 Cond = Op0Op1;
683 IfSet = Op0Op0;
684
685 if (isVSplat(Op1Op0, InvMask, IsLittleEndian) &&
686 Mask.getBitWidth() == InvMask.getBitWidth() && Mask == ~InvMask)
687 IfClr = Op1Op1;
688 else if (isVSplat(Op1Op1, InvMask, IsLittleEndian) &&
689 Mask.getBitWidth() == InvMask.getBitWidth() && Mask == ~InvMask)
690 IfClr = Op1Op0;
691
692 IsConstantMask = true;
693 }
694
695 // If IfClr is not yet set, try looking for a non-constant match.
696 // IfClr will be set if we find a valid match amongst the eight
697 // possibilities.
698 if (!IfClr.getNode()) {
699 if (isBitwiseInverse(Op0Op0, Op1Op0)) {
700 Cond = Op1Op0;
701 IfSet = Op1Op1;
702 IfClr = Op0Op1;
703 } else if (isBitwiseInverse(Op0Op1, Op1Op0)) {
704 Cond = Op1Op0;
705 IfSet = Op1Op1;
706 IfClr = Op0Op0;
707 } else if (isBitwiseInverse(Op0Op0, Op1Op1)) {
708 Cond = Op1Op1;
709 IfSet = Op1Op0;
710 IfClr = Op0Op1;
711 } else if (isBitwiseInverse(Op0Op1, Op1Op1)) {
712 Cond = Op1Op1;
713 IfSet = Op1Op0;
714 IfClr = Op0Op0;
715 } else if (isBitwiseInverse(Op1Op0, Op0Op0)) {
716 Cond = Op0Op0;
717 IfSet = Op0Op1;
718 IfClr = Op1Op1;
719 } else if (isBitwiseInverse(Op1Op1, Op0Op0)) {
720 Cond = Op0Op0;
721 IfSet = Op0Op1;
722 IfClr = Op1Op0;
723 } else if (isBitwiseInverse(Op1Op0, Op0Op1)) {
724 Cond = Op0Op1;
725 IfSet = Op0Op0;
726 IfClr = Op1Op1;
727 } else if (isBitwiseInverse(Op1Op1, Op0Op1)) {
728 Cond = Op0Op1;
729 IfSet = Op0Op0;
730 IfClr = Op1Op0;
731 }
732 }
733
734 // At this point, IfClr will be set if we have a valid match.
735 if (!IfClr.getNode())
736 return SDValue();
737
738 assert(Cond.getNode() && IfSet.getNode());
739
740 // Fold degenerate cases.
741 if (IsConstantMask) {
742 if (Mask.isAllOnesValue())
743 return IfSet;
744 else if (Mask == 0)
745 return IfClr;
746 }
747
748 // Transform the DAG into an equivalent VSELECT.
749 return DAG.getNode(ISD::VSELECT, SDLoc(N), Ty, Cond, IfSet, IfClr);
750 }
751
752 return SDValue();
753}
754
755static bool shouldTransformMulToShiftsAddsSubs(APInt C, EVT VT,
756 SelectionDAG &DAG,
757 const MipsSubtarget &Subtarget) {
758 // Estimate the number of operations the below transform will turn a
759 // constant multiply into. The number is approximately equal to the minimal
760 // number of powers of two that constant can be broken down to by adding
761 // or subtracting them.
762 //
763 // If we have taken more than 12[1] / 8[2] steps to attempt the
764 // optimization for a native sized value, it is more than likely that this
765 // optimization will make things worse.
766 //
767 // [1] MIPS64 requires 6 instructions at most to materialize any constant,
768 // multiplication requires at least 4 cycles, but another cycle (or two)
769 // to retrieve the result from the HI/LO registers.
770 //
771 // [2] For MIPS32, more than 8 steps is expensive as the constant could be
772 // materialized in 2 instructions, multiplication requires at least 4
773 // cycles, but another cycle (or two) to retrieve the result from the
774 // HI/LO registers.
775 //
776 // TODO:
777 // - MaxSteps needs to consider the `VT` of the constant for the current
778 // target.
779 // - Consider to perform this optimization after type legalization.
780 // That allows to remove a workaround for types not supported natively.
781 // - Take in account `-Os, -Oz` flags because this optimization
782 // increases code size.
783 unsigned MaxSteps = Subtarget.isABI_O32() ? 8 : 12;
784
785 SmallVector<APInt, 16> WorkStack(1, C);
786 unsigned Steps = 0;
787 unsigned BitWidth = C.getBitWidth();
788
789 while (!WorkStack.empty()) {
790 APInt Val = WorkStack.pop_back_val();
791
792 if (Val == 0 || Val == 1)
793 continue;
794
795 if (Steps >= MaxSteps)
796 return false;
797
798 if (Val.isPowerOf2()) {
799 ++Steps;
800 continue;
801 }
802
803 APInt Floor = APInt(BitWidth, 1) << Val.logBase2();
804 APInt Ceil = Val.isNegative() ? APInt(BitWidth, 0)
805 : APInt(BitWidth, 1) << C.ceilLogBase2();
806 if ((Val - Floor).ule(Ceil - Val)) {
807 WorkStack.push_back(Floor);
808 WorkStack.push_back(Val - Floor);
809 } else {
810 WorkStack.push_back(Ceil);
811 WorkStack.push_back(Ceil - Val);
812 }
813
814 ++Steps;
815 }
816
817 // If the value being multiplied is not supported natively, we have to pay
818 // an additional legalization cost, conservatively assume an increase in the
819 // cost of 3 instructions per step. This values for this heuristic were
820 // determined experimentally.
821 unsigned RegisterSize = DAG.getTargetLoweringInfo()
822 .getRegisterType(*DAG.getContext(), VT)
823 .getSizeInBits();
824 Steps *= (VT.getSizeInBits() != RegisterSize) * 3;
825 if (Steps > 27)
826 return false;
827
828 return true;
829}
830
831static SDValue genConstMult(SDValue X, APInt C, const SDLoc &DL, EVT VT,
832 EVT ShiftTy, SelectionDAG &DAG) {
833 // Return 0.
834 if (C == 0)
835 return DAG.getConstant(0, DL, VT);
836
837 // Return x.
838 if (C == 1)
839 return X;
840
841 // If c is power of 2, return (shl x, log2(c)).
842 if (C.isPowerOf2())
843 return DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, DL, VT, X,
844 DAG.getConstant(C.logBase2(), DL, ShiftTy));
845
846 unsigned BitWidth = C.getBitWidth();
847 APInt Floor = APInt(BitWidth, 1) << C.logBase2();
848 APInt Ceil = C.isNegative() ? APInt(BitWidth, 0) :
849 APInt(BitWidth, 1) << C.ceilLogBase2();
850
851 // If |c - floor_c| <= |c - ceil_c|,
852 // where floor_c = pow(2, floor(log2(c))) and ceil_c = pow(2, ceil(log2(c))),
853 // return (add constMult(x, floor_c), constMult(x, c - floor_c)).
854 if ((C - Floor).ule(Ceil - C)) {
855 SDValue Op0 = genConstMult(X, Floor, DL, VT, ShiftTy, DAG);
856 SDValue Op1 = genConstMult(X, C - Floor, DL, VT, ShiftTy, DAG);
857 return DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, DL, VT, Op0, Op1);
858 }
859
860 // If |c - floor_c| > |c - ceil_c|,
861 // return (sub constMult(x, ceil_c), constMult(x, ceil_c - c)).
862 SDValue Op0 = genConstMult(X, Ceil, DL, VT, ShiftTy, DAG);
863 SDValue Op1 = genConstMult(X, Ceil - C, DL, VT, ShiftTy, DAG);
864 return DAG.getNode(ISD::SUB, DL, VT, Op0, Op1);
865}
866
867static SDValue performMULCombine(SDNode *N, SelectionDAG &DAG,
868 const TargetLowering::DAGCombinerInfo &DCI,
869 const MipsSETargetLowering *TL,
870 const MipsSubtarget &Subtarget) {
871 EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
872
873 if (ConstantSDNode *C = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(N->getOperand(1)))
874 if (!VT.isVector() && shouldTransformMulToShiftsAddsSubs(
875 C->getAPIntValue(), VT, DAG, Subtarget)) {
876 assert(VT.isInteger());
877 return genConstMult(N->getOperand(0), C->getAPIntValue(), SDLoc(N), VT,
878 TL->getScalarShiftAmountTy(DAG.getDataLayout(), VT),
879 DAG);
880 }
881 return SDValue(N, 0);
882}
883
884static SDValue performDSPShiftCombine(unsigned Opc, SDNode *N, EVT Ty,
885 SelectionDAG &DAG,
886 const MipsSubtarget &Subtarget) {
887 // See if this is a vector splat immediate node.
888 APInt SplatValue, SplatUndef;
889 unsigned SplatBitSize;
890 bool HasAnyUndefs;
891 unsigned EltSize = Ty.getScalarSizeInBits();
892 BuildVectorSDNode *BV = dyn_cast<BuildVectorSDNode>(N->getOperand(1));
893
894 if (!Subtarget.hasDSP())
895 return SDValue();
896
897 if (!BV ||
898 !BV->isConstantSplat(SplatValue, SplatUndef, SplatBitSize, HasAnyUndefs,
899 EltSize, !Subtarget.isLittle()) ||
900 (SplatBitSize != EltSize) ||
901 (SplatValue.getZExtValue() >= EltSize))
902 return SDValue();
903
904 SDLoc DL(N);
905 return DAG.getNode(Opc, DL, Ty, N->getOperand(0),
906 DAG.getConstant(SplatValue.getZExtValue(), DL, MVT::i32));
907}
908
909static SDValue performSHLCombine(SDNode *N, SelectionDAG &DAG,
910 TargetLowering::DAGCombinerInfo &DCI,
911 const MipsSubtarget &Subtarget) {
912 EVT Ty = N->getValueType(0);
913
914 if ((Ty != MVT::v2i16) && (Ty != MVT::v4i8))
915 return SDValue();
916
917 return performDSPShiftCombine(MipsISD::SHLL_DSP, N, Ty, DAG, Subtarget);
918}
919
920// Fold sign-extensions into MipsISD::VEXTRACT_[SZ]EXT_ELT for MSA and fold
921// constant splats into MipsISD::SHRA_DSP for DSPr2.
922//
923// Performs the following transformations:
924// - Changes MipsISD::VEXTRACT_[SZ]EXT_ELT to sign extension if its
925// sign/zero-extension is completely overwritten by the new one performed by
926// the ISD::SRA and ISD::SHL nodes.
927// - Removes redundant sign extensions performed by an ISD::SRA and ISD::SHL
928// sequence.
929//
930// See performDSPShiftCombine for more information about the transformation
931// used for DSPr2.
932static SDValue performSRACombine(SDNode *N, SelectionDAG &DAG,
933 TargetLowering::DAGCombinerInfo &DCI,
934 const MipsSubtarget &Subtarget) {
935 EVT Ty = N->getValueType(0);
936
937 if (Subtarget.hasMSA()) {
938 SDValue Op0 = N->getOperand(0);
939 SDValue Op1 = N->getOperand(1);
940
941 // (sra (shl (MipsVExtract[SZ]Ext $a, $b, $c), imm:$d), imm:$d)
942 // where $d + sizeof($c) == 32
943 // or $d + sizeof($c) <= 32 and SExt
944 // -> (MipsVExtractSExt $a, $b, $c)
945 if (Op0->getOpcode() == ISD::SHL && Op1 == Op0->getOperand(1)) {
946 SDValue Op0Op0 = Op0->getOperand(0);
947 ConstantSDNode *ShAmount = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op1);
948
949 if (!ShAmount)
950 return SDValue();
951
952 if (Op0Op0->getOpcode() != MipsISD::VEXTRACT_SEXT_ELT &&
953 Op0Op0->getOpcode() != MipsISD::VEXTRACT_ZEXT_ELT)
954 return SDValue();
955
956 EVT ExtendTy = cast<VTSDNode>(Op0Op0->getOperand(2))->getVT();
957 unsigned TotalBits = ShAmount->getZExtValue() + ExtendTy.getSizeInBits();
958
959 if (TotalBits == 32 ||
960 (Op0Op0->getOpcode() == MipsISD::VEXTRACT_SEXT_ELT &&
961 TotalBits <= 32)) {
962 SDValue Ops[] = { Op0Op0->getOperand(0), Op0Op0->getOperand(1),
963 Op0Op0->getOperand(2) };
964 return DAG.getNode(MipsISD::VEXTRACT_SEXT_ELT, SDLoc(Op0Op0),
965 Op0Op0->getVTList(),
966 makeArrayRef(Ops, Op0Op0->getNumOperands()));
967 }
968 }
969 }
970
971 if ((Ty != MVT::v2i16) && ((Ty != MVT::v4i8) || !Subtarget.hasDSPR2()))
972 return SDValue();
973
974 return performDSPShiftCombine(MipsISD::SHRA_DSP, N, Ty, DAG, Subtarget);
975}
976
977
978static SDValue performSRLCombine(SDNode *N, SelectionDAG &DAG,
979 TargetLowering::DAGCombinerInfo &DCI,
980 const MipsSubtarget &Subtarget) {
981 EVT Ty = N->getValueType(0);
982
983 if (((Ty != MVT::v2i16) || !Subtarget.hasDSPR2()) && (Ty != MVT::v4i8))
984 return SDValue();
985
986 return performDSPShiftCombine(MipsISD::SHRL_DSP, N, Ty, DAG, Subtarget);
987}
988
989static bool isLegalDSPCondCode(EVT Ty, ISD::CondCode CC) {
990 bool IsV216 = (Ty == MVT::v2i16);
991
992 switch (CC) {
993 case ISD::SETEQ:
994 case ISD::SETNE: return true;
995 case ISD::SETLT:
996 case ISD::SETLE:
997 case ISD::SETGT:
998 case ISD::SETGE: return IsV216;
999 case ISD::SETULT:
1000 case ISD::SETULE:
1001 case ISD::SETUGT:
1002 case ISD::SETUGE: return !IsV216;
1003 default: return false;
1004 }
1005}
1006
1007static SDValue performSETCCCombine(SDNode *N, SelectionDAG &DAG) {
1008 EVT Ty = N->getValueType(0);
1009
1010 if ((Ty != MVT::v2i16) && (Ty != MVT::v4i8))
1011 return SDValue();
1012
1013 if (!isLegalDSPCondCode(Ty, cast<CondCodeSDNode>(N->getOperand(2))->get()))
1014 return SDValue();
1015
1016 return DAG.getNode(MipsISD::SETCC_DSP, SDLoc(N), Ty, N->getOperand(0),
1017 N->getOperand(1), N->getOperand(2));
1018}
1019
1020static SDValue performVSELECTCombine(SDNode *N, SelectionDAG &DAG) {
1021 EVT Ty = N->getValueType(0);
1022
1023 if (Ty == MVT::v2i16 || Ty == MVT::v4i8) {
1024 SDValue SetCC = N->getOperand(0);
1025
1026 if (SetCC.getOpcode() != MipsISD::SETCC_DSP)
1027 return SDValue();
1028
1029 return DAG.getNode(MipsISD::SELECT_CC_DSP, SDLoc(N), Ty,
1030 SetCC.getOperand(0), SetCC.getOperand(1),
1031 N->getOperand(1), N->getOperand(2), SetCC.getOperand(2));
1032 }
1033
1034 return SDValue();
1035}
1036
1037static SDValue performXORCombine(SDNode *N, SelectionDAG &DAG,
1038 const MipsSubtarget &Subtarget) {
1039 EVT Ty = N->getValueType(0);
1040
1041 if (Subtarget.hasMSA() && Ty.is128BitVector() && Ty.isInteger()) {
1042 // Try the following combines:
1043 // (xor (or $a, $b), (build_vector allones))
1044 // (xor (or $a, $b), (bitcast (build_vector allones)))
1045 SDValue Op0 = N->getOperand(0);
1046 SDValue Op1 = N->getOperand(1);
1047 SDValue NotOp;
1048
1049 if (ISD::isBuildVectorAllOnes(Op0.getNode()))
1050 NotOp = Op1;
1051 else if (ISD::isBuildVectorAllOnes(Op1.getNode()))
1052 NotOp = Op0;
1053 else
1054 return SDValue();
1055
1056 if (NotOp->getOpcode() == ISD::OR)
1057 return DAG.getNode(MipsISD::VNOR, SDLoc(N), Ty, NotOp->getOperand(0),
1058 NotOp->getOperand(1));
1059 }
1060
1061 return SDValue();
1062}
1063
1064SDValue
1065MipsSETargetLowering::PerformDAGCombine(SDNode *N, DAGCombinerInfo &DCI) const {
1066 SelectionDAG &DAG = DCI.DAG;
1067 SDValue Val;
1068
1069 switch (N->getOpcode()) {
1070 case ISD::AND:
1071 Val = performANDCombine(N, DAG, DCI, Subtarget);
1072 break;
1073 case ISD::OR:
1074 Val = performORCombine(N, DAG, DCI, Subtarget);
1075 break;
1076 case ISD::MUL:
1077 return performMULCombine(N, DAG, DCI, this, Subtarget);
1078 case ISD::SHL:
1079 Val = performSHLCombine(N, DAG, DCI, Subtarget);
1080 break;
1081 case ISD::SRA:
1082 return performSRACombine(N, DAG, DCI, Subtarget);
1083 case ISD::SRL:
1084 return performSRLCombine(N, DAG, DCI, Subtarget);
1085 case ISD::VSELECT:
1086 return performVSELECTCombine(N, DAG);
1087 case ISD::XOR:
1088 Val = performXORCombine(N, DAG, Subtarget);
1089 break;
1090 case ISD::SETCC:
1091 Val = performSETCCCombine(N, DAG);
1092 break;
1093 }
1094
1095 if (Val.getNode()) {
1096 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "\nMipsSE DAG Combine:\n";
1097 N->printrWithDepth(dbgs(), &DAG); dbgs() << "\n=> \n";
1098 Val.getNode()->printrWithDepth(dbgs(), &DAG); dbgs() << "\n");
1099 return Val;
1100 }
1101
1102 return MipsTargetLowering::PerformDAGCombine(N, DCI);
1103}

1195
1196bool MipsSETargetLowering::isEligibleForTailCallOptimization(
1197 const CCState &CCInfo, unsigned NextStackOffset,
1198 const MipsFunctionInfo &FI) const {
1199 if (!UseMipsTailCalls)
1200 return false;
1201
1202 // Exception has to be cleared with eret.
1203 if (FI.isISR())
1204 return false;
1205
1206 // Return false if either the callee or caller has a byval argument.
1207 if (CCInfo.getInRegsParamsCount() > 0 || FI.hasByvalArg())
1208 return false;
1209
1210 // Return true if the callee's argument area is no larger than the
1211 // caller's.
1212 return NextStackOffset <= FI.getIncomingArgSize();
1213}

1215void MipsSETargetLowering::
1216getOpndList(SmallVectorImpl<SDValue> &Ops,

1218 bool IsPICCall, bool GlobalOrExternal, bool InternalLinkage,
1219 bool IsCallReloc, CallLoweringInfo &CLI, SDValue Callee,
1220 SDValue Chain) const {
1221 Ops.push_back(Callee);
1222 MipsTargetLowering::getOpndList(Ops, RegsToPass, IsPICCall, GlobalOrExternal,
1223 InternalLinkage, IsCallReloc, CLI, Callee,
1224 Chain);
1225}
1226
1227SDValue MipsSETargetLowering::lowerLOAD(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
1228 LoadSDNode &Nd = *cast<LoadSDNode>(Op);
1229
1230 if (Nd.getMemoryVT() != MVT::f64 || !NoDPLoadStore)
1231 return MipsTargetLowering::lowerLOAD(Op, DAG);
1232
1233 // Replace a double precision load with two i32 loads and a buildpair64.
1234 SDLoc DL(Op);
1235 SDValue Ptr = Nd.getBasePtr(), Chain = Nd.getChain();
1236
1237 // i32 load from lower address.
1238 SDValue Lo = DAG.getLoad(MVT::i32, DL, Chain, Ptr, MachinePointerInfo(),
1239 Nd.getAlignment(), Nd.getMemOperand()->getFlags());
1240
1241 // i32 load from higher address.
1242 Ptr = DAG.getPointerAdd(DL, Ptr, 4);
1243 SDValue Hi = DAG.getLoad(
1244 MVT::i32, DL, Lo.getValue(1), Ptr, MachinePointerInfo(),
1245 std::min(Nd.getAlignment(), 4U), Nd.getMemOperand()->getFlags());
1246
1247 if (!Subtarget.isLittle())
1248 std::swap(Lo, Hi);
1249
1250 SDValue BP = DAG.getNode(MipsISD::BuildPairF64, DL, MVT::f64, Lo, Hi);
1251 SDValue Ops[2] = {BP, Hi.getValue(1)};
1252 return DAG.getMergeValues(Ops, DL);
1253}
1254
1255SDValue MipsSETargetLowering::lowerSTORE(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
1256 StoreSDNode &Nd = *cast<StoreSDNode>(Op);
1257
1258 if (Nd.getMemoryVT() != MVT::f64 || !NoDPLoadStore)
1259 return MipsTargetLowering::lowerSTORE(Op, DAG);
1260
1261 // Replace a double precision store with two extractelement64s and i32 stores.
1262 SDLoc DL(Op);
1263 SDValue Val = Nd.getValue(), Ptr = Nd.getBasePtr(), Chain = Nd.getChain();
1264 SDValue Lo = DAG.getNode(MipsISD::ExtractElementF64, DL, MVT::i32,
1265 Val, DAG.getConstant(0, DL, MVT::i32));
1266 SDValue Hi = DAG.getNode(MipsISD::ExtractElementF64, DL, MVT::i32,
1267 Val, DAG.getConstant(1, DL, MVT::i32));
1268
1269 if (!Subtarget.isLittle())
1270 std::swap(Lo, Hi);
1271
1272 // i32 store to lower address.
1273 Chain =
1274 DAG.getStore(Chain, DL, Lo, Ptr, MachinePointerInfo(), Nd.getAlignment(),
1275 Nd.getMemOperand()->getFlags(), Nd.getAAInfo());
1276
1277 // i32 store to higher address.
1278 Ptr = DAG.getPointerAdd(DL, Ptr, 4);
1279 return DAG.getStore(Chain, DL, Hi, Ptr, MachinePointerInfo(),
1280 std::min(Nd.getAlignment(), 4U),
1281 Nd.getMemOperand()->getFlags(), Nd.getAAInfo());
1282}
1283
1284SDValue MipsSETargetLowering::lowerBITCAST(SDValue Op,
1285 SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
1286 SDLoc DL(Op);
1287 MVT Src = Op.getOperand(0).getValueType().getSimpleVT();
1288 MVT Dest = Op.getValueType().getSimpleVT();
1289
1290 // Bitcast i64 to double.
1291 if (Src == MVT::i64 && Dest == MVT::f64) {
1292 SDValue Lo = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_ELEMENT, DL, MVT::i32,
1293 Op.getOperand(0), DAG.getIntPtrConstant(0, DL));
1294 SDValue Hi = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_ELEMENT, DL, MVT::i32,
1295 Op.getOperand(0), DAG.getIntPtrConstant(1, DL));
1296 return DAG.getNode(MipsISD::BuildPairF64, DL, MVT::f64, Lo, Hi);
1297 }
1298
1299 // Bitcast double to i64.
1300 if (Src == MVT::f64 && Dest == MVT::i64) {
1301 SDValue Lo =
1302 DAG.getNode(MipsISD::ExtractElementF64, DL, MVT::i32, Op.getOperand(0),
1303 DAG.getConstant(0, DL, MVT::i32));
1304 SDValue Hi =
1305 DAG.getNode(MipsISD::ExtractElementF64, DL, MVT::i32, Op.getOperand(0),
1306 DAG.getConstant(1, DL, MVT::i32));
1307 return DAG.getNode(ISD::BUILD_PAIR, DL, MVT::i64, Lo, Hi);
1308 }
1309
1310 // Skip other cases of bitcast and use default lowering.
1311 return SDValue();
1312}
1313
1314SDValue MipsSETargetLowering::lowerMulDiv(SDValue Op, unsigned NewOpc,
1315 bool HasLo, bool HasHi,
1316 SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
1317 // MIPS32r6/MIPS64r6 removed accumulator based multiplies.
1318 assert(!Subtarget.hasMips32r6());
1319
1320 EVT Ty = Op.getOperand(0).getValueType();
1321 SDLoc DL(Op);
1322 SDValue Mult = DAG.getNode(NewOpc, DL, MVT::Untyped,
1323 Op.getOperand(0), Op.getOperand(1));
1324 SDValue Lo, Hi;
1325
1326 if (HasLo)
1327 Lo = DAG.getNode(MipsISD::MFLO, DL, Ty, Mult);
1328 if (HasHi)
1329 Hi = DAG.getNode(MipsISD::MFHI, DL, Ty, Mult);
1330
1331 if (!HasLo || !HasHi)
1332 return HasLo ? Lo : Hi;
1333
1334 SDValue Vals[] = { Lo, Hi };
1335 return DAG.getMergeValues(Vals, DL);
1336}
1337
1338static SDValue initAccumulator(SDValue In, const SDLoc &DL, SelectionDAG &DAG) {
1339 SDValue InLo = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_ELEMENT, DL, MVT::i32, In,
1340 DAG.getConstant(0, DL, MVT::i32));
1341 SDValue InHi = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_ELEMENT, DL, MVT::i32, In,
1342 DAG.getConstant(1, DL, MVT::i32));
1343 return DAG.getNode(MipsISD::MTLOHI, DL, MVT::Untyped, InLo, InHi);
1344}
1345
1346static SDValue extractLOHI(SDValue Op, const SDLoc &DL, SelectionDAG &DAG) {
1347 SDValue Lo = DAG.getNode(MipsISD::MFLO, DL, MVT::i32, Op);
1348 SDValue Hi = DAG.getNode(MipsISD::MFHI, DL, MVT::i32, Op);
1349 return DAG.getNode(ISD::BUILD_PAIR, DL, MVT::i64, Lo, Hi);
1350}
1351
1352// This function expands mips intrinsic nodes which have 64-bit input operands
1353// or output values.
1354//
1355// out64 = intrinsic-node in64
1356// =>
1357// lo = copy (extract-element (in64, 0))
1358// hi = copy (extract-element (in64, 1))
1359// mips-specific-node
1360// v0 = copy lo
1361// v1 = copy hi
1362// out64 = merge-values (v0, v1)
1363//
1364static SDValue lowerDSPIntr(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG, unsigned Opc) {
1365 SDLoc DL(Op);
1366 bool HasChainIn = Op->getOperand(0).getValueType() == MVT::Other;
1367 SmallVector<SDValue, 3> Ops;
1368 unsigned OpNo = 0;
1369
1370 // See if Op has a chain input.
1371 if (HasChainIn)
1372 Ops.push_back(Op->getOperand(OpNo++));
1373
1374 // The next operand is the intrinsic opcode.
1375 assert(Op->getOperand(OpNo).getOpcode() == ISD::TargetConstant);
1376
1377 // See if the next operand has type i64.
1378 SDValue Opnd = Op->getOperand(++OpNo), In64;
1379
1380 if (Opnd.getValueType() == MVT::i64)
1381 In64 = initAccumulator(Opnd, DL, DAG);
1382 else
1383 Ops.push_back(Opnd);
1384
1385 // Push the remaining operands.
1386 for (++OpNo ; OpNo < Op->getNumOperands(); ++OpNo)
1387 Ops.push_back(Op->getOperand(OpNo));
1388
1389 // Add In64 to the end of the list.
1390 if (In64.getNode())
1391 Ops.push_back(In64);
1392
1393 // Scan output.
1394 SmallVector<EVT, 2> ResTys;
1395
1396 for (SDNode::value_iterator I = Op->value_begin(), E = Op->value_end();
1397 I != E; ++I)
1398 ResTys.push_back((*I == MVT::i64) ? MVT::Untyped : *I);
1399
1400 // Create node.
1401 SDValue Val = DAG.getNode(Opc, DL, ResTys, Ops);
1402 SDValue Out = (ResTys[0] == MVT::Untyped) ? extractLOHI(Val, DL, DAG) : Val;
1403
1404 if (!HasChainIn)
1405 return Out;
1406
1407 assert(Val->getValueType(1) == MVT::Other);
1408 SDValue Vals[] = { Out, SDValue(Val.getNode(), 1) };
1409 return DAG.getMergeValues(Vals, DL);
1410}
1411
1412// Lower an MSA copy intrinsic into the specified SelectionDAG node
1413static SDValue lowerMSACopyIntr(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG, unsigned Opc) {
1414 SDLoc DL(Op);
1415 SDValue Vec = Op->getOperand(1);
1416 SDValue Idx = Op->getOperand(2);
1417 EVT ResTy = Op->getValueType(0);
1418 EVT EltTy = Vec->getValueType(0).getVectorElementType();
1419
1420 SDValue Result = DAG.getNode(Opc, DL, ResTy, Vec, Idx,
1421 DAG.getValueType(EltTy));
1422
1423 return Result;
1424}
1425
1426static SDValue lowerMSASplatZExt(SDValue Op, unsigned OpNr, SelectionDAG &DAG) {
1427 EVT ResVecTy = Op->getValueType(0);
1428 EVT ViaVecTy = ResVecTy;
1429 bool BigEndian = !DAG.getSubtarget().getTargetTriple().isLittleEndian();
1430 SDLoc DL(Op);
1431
1432 // When ResVecTy == MVT::v2i64, LaneA is the upper 32 bits of the lane and
1433 // LaneB is the lower 32-bits. Otherwise LaneA and LaneB are alternating
1434 // lanes.
1435 SDValue LaneA = Op->getOperand(OpNr);
1436 SDValue LaneB;
1437
1438 if (ResVecTy == MVT::v2i64) {
1439 // In case of the index being passed as an immediate value, set the upper
1440 // lane to 0 so that the splati.d instruction can be matched.
1441 if (isa<ConstantSDNode>(LaneA))
1442 LaneB = DAG.getConstant(0, DL, MVT::i32);
1443 // Having the index passed in a register, set the upper lane to the same
1444 // value as the lower - this results in the BUILD_VECTOR node not being
1445 // expanded through stack. This way we are able to pattern match the set of
1446 // nodes created here to splat.d.
1447 else
1448 LaneB = LaneA;
1449 ViaVecTy = MVT::v4i32;
1450 if(BigEndian)
1451 std::swap(LaneA, LaneB);
1452 } else
1453 LaneB = LaneA;
1454
1455 SDValue Ops[16] = { LaneA, LaneB, LaneA, LaneB, LaneA, LaneB, LaneA, LaneB,
1456 LaneA, LaneB, LaneA, LaneB, LaneA, LaneB, LaneA, LaneB };
1457
1458 SDValue Result = DAG.getBuildVector(
1459 ViaVecTy, DL, makeArrayRef(Ops, ViaVecTy.getVectorNumElements()));
1460
1461 if (ViaVecTy != ResVecTy) {
1462 SDValue One = DAG.getConstant(1, DL, ViaVecTy);
1463 Result = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, ResVecTy,
1464 DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, DL, ViaVecTy, Result, One));
1465 }
1466
1467 return Result;
1468}
1469
1470static SDValue lowerMSASplatImm(SDValue Op, unsigned ImmOp, SelectionDAG &DAG,
1471 bool IsSigned = false) {
1472 auto *CImm = cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op->getOperand(ImmOp));
1473 return DAG.getConstant(
1474 APInt(Op->getValueType(0).getScalarType().getSizeInBits(),
1475 IsSigned ? CImm->getSExtValue() : CImm->getZExtValue(), IsSigned),
1476 SDLoc(Op), Op->getValueType(0));
1477}
1478
1479static SDValue getBuildVectorSplat(EVT VecTy, SDValue SplatValue,
1480 bool BigEndian, SelectionDAG &DAG) {
1481 EVT ViaVecTy = VecTy;
1482 SDValue SplatValueA = SplatValue;
1483 SDValue SplatValueB = SplatValue;
1484 SDLoc DL(SplatValue);
1485
1486 if (VecTy == MVT::v2i64) {
1487 // v2i64 BUILD_VECTOR must be performed via v4i32 so split into i32's.
1488 ViaVecTy = MVT::v4i32;
1489
1490 SplatValueA = DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, DL, MVT::i32, SplatValue);
1491 SplatValueB = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, DL, MVT::i64, SplatValue,
1492 DAG.getConstant(32, DL, MVT::i32));
1493 SplatValueB = DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, DL, MVT::i32, SplatValueB);
1494 }
1495
1496 // We currently hold the parts in little endian order. Swap them if
1497 // necessary.
1498 if (BigEndian)
1499 std::swap(SplatValueA, SplatValueB);
1500
1501 SDValue Ops[16] = { SplatValueA, SplatValueB, SplatValueA, SplatValueB,
1502 SplatValueA, SplatValueB, SplatValueA, SplatValueB,
1503 SplatValueA, SplatValueB, SplatValueA, SplatValueB,
1504 SplatValueA, SplatValueB, SplatValueA, SplatValueB };
1505
1506 SDValue Result = DAG.getBuildVector(
1507 ViaVecTy, DL, makeArrayRef(Ops, ViaVecTy.getVectorNumElements()));
1508
1509 if (VecTy != ViaVecTy)
1510 Result = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, VecTy, Result);
1511
1512 return Result;
1513}
1514
1515static SDValue lowerMSABinaryBitImmIntr(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG,
1516 unsigned Opc, SDValue Imm,
1517 bool BigEndian) {
1518 EVT VecTy = Op->getValueType(0);
1519 SDValue Exp2Imm;
1520 SDLoc DL(Op);
1521
1522 // The DAG Combiner can't constant fold bitcasted vectors yet so we must do it
1523 // here for now.
1524 if (VecTy == MVT::v2i64) {
1525 if (ConstantSDNode *CImm = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Imm)) {
1526 APInt BitImm = APInt(64, 1) << CImm->getAPIntValue();
1527
1528 SDValue BitImmHiOp = DAG.getConstant(BitImm.lshr(32).trunc(32), DL,
1529 MVT::i32);
1530 SDValue BitImmLoOp = DAG.getConstant(BitImm.trunc(32), DL, MVT::i32);
1531
1532 if (BigEndian)
1533 std::swap(BitImmLoOp, BitImmHiOp);
1534
1535 Exp2Imm = DAG.getNode(
1536 ISD::BITCAST, DL, MVT::v2i64,
1537 DAG.getBuildVector(MVT::v4i32, DL,
1538 {BitImmLoOp, BitImmHiOp, BitImmLoOp, BitImmHiOp}));
1539 }
1540 }
1541
1542 if (!Exp2Imm.getNode()) {
1543 // We couldnt constant fold, do a vector shift instead
1544
1545 // Extend i32 to i64 if necessary. Sign or zero extend doesn't matter since
1546 // only values 0-63 are valid.
1547 if (VecTy == MVT::v2i64)
1548 Imm = DAG.getNode(ISD::ZERO_EXTEND, DL, MVT::i64, Imm);
1549
1550 Exp2Imm = getBuildVectorSplat(VecTy, Imm, BigEndian, DAG);
1551
1552 Exp2Imm = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, DL, VecTy, DAG.getConstant(1, DL, VecTy),
1553 Exp2Imm);
1554 }
1555
1556 return DAG.getNode(Opc, DL, VecTy, Op->getOperand(1), Exp2Imm);
1557}
1558
1559static SDValue truncateVecElts(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG) {
1560 SDLoc DL(Op);
1561 EVT ResTy = Op->getValueType(0);
1562 SDValue Vec = Op->getOperand(2);
1563 bool BigEndian = !DAG.getSubtarget().getTargetTriple().isLittleEndian();
1564 MVT ResEltTy = ResTy == MVT::v2i64 ? MVT::i64 : MVT::i32;
1565 SDValue ConstValue = DAG.getConstant(Vec.getScalarValueSizeInBits() - 1,
1566 DL, ResEltTy);
1567 SDValue SplatVec = getBuildVectorSplat(ResTy, ConstValue, BigEndian, DAG);
1568
1569 return DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, DL, ResTy, Vec, SplatVec);
1570}
1571
1572static SDValue lowerMSABitClear(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG) {
1573 EVT ResTy = Op->getValueType(0);
1574 SDLoc DL(Op);
1575 SDValue One = DAG.getConstant(1, DL, ResTy);
1576 SDValue Bit = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, DL, ResTy, One, truncateVecElts(Op, DAG));
1577
1578 return DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, DL, ResTy, Op->getOperand(1),
1579 DAG.getNOT(DL, Bit, ResTy));
1580}

1582static SDValue lowerMSABitClearImm(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG) {
1583 SDLoc DL(Op);
1584 EVT ResTy = Op->getValueType(0);
1585 APInt BitImm = APInt(ResTy.getScalarSizeInBits(), 1)
1586 << cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op->getOperand(2))->getAPIntValue();
1587 SDValue BitMask = DAG.getConstant(~BitImm, DL, ResTy);
1588
1589 return DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, DL, ResTy, Op->getOperand(1), BitMask);
1590}
1591
1592SDValue MipsSETargetLowering::lowerINTRINSIC_WO_CHAIN(SDValue Op,
1593 SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
1594 SDLoc DL(Op);
1595 unsigned Intrinsic = cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op->getOperand(0))->getZExtValue();
1596 switch (Intrinsic) {
1597 default:
1598 return SDValue();
1599 case Intrinsic::mips_captable_get:
1600 if (ABI.UsesCapabilityTable())
1601 return getCapGlobalReg(DAG, CapType);
1602 DAG.getContext()->diagnose(DiagnosticInfoUnsupported(
1603 DAG.getMachineFunction().getFunction(),
1604 "the current ABI does not use a captable", DL.getDebugLoc()));
1605 return DAG.getNullCapability(DL, CapType);
1606 case Intrinsic::mips_shilo:
1607 return lowerDSPIntr(Op, DAG, MipsISD::SHILO);
1608 case Intrinsic::mips_dpau_h_qbl:

2354static SDValue lowerMSALoadIntr(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG, unsigned Intr,
2355 const MipsSubtarget &Subtarget) {
2356 SDLoc DL(Op);
2357 SDValue ChainIn = Op->getOperand(0);
2358 SDValue Address = Op->getOperand(2);
2359 SDValue Offset = Op->getOperand(3);
2360 EVT ResTy = Op->getValueType(0);
2361 EVT PtrTy = Address->getValueType(0);
2362
2363 // For N64 addresses have the underlying type MVT::i64. This intrinsic
2364 // however takes an i32 signed constant offset. The actual type of the
2365 // intrinsic is a scaled signed i10.
2366 if (Subtarget.isABI_N64())
2367 Offset = DAG.getNode(ISD::SIGN_EXTEND, DL, PtrTy, Offset);
2368
2369 Address = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, DL, PtrTy, Address, Offset);
2370 return DAG.getLoad(ResTy, DL, ChainIn, Address, MachinePointerInfo(),
2371 /* Alignment = */ 16);
2372}

2428static SDValue lowerMSAStoreIntr(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG, unsigned Intr,

2463// Lower ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT into MipsISD::VEXTRACT_SEXT_ELT.
2464//
2465// The non-value bits resulting from ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT are undefined. We
2466// choose to sign-extend but we could have equally chosen zero-extend. The
2467// DAGCombiner will fold any sign/zero extension of the ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT
2468// result into this node later (possibly changing it to a zero-extend in the
2469// process).
2470SDValue MipsSETargetLowering::
2471lowerEXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
2472 SDLoc DL(Op);
2473 EVT ResTy = Op->getValueType(0);
2474 SDValue Op0 = Op->getOperand(0);
2475 EVT VecTy = Op0->getValueType(0);
2476
2477 if (!VecTy.is128BitVector())
2478 return SDValue();
2479
2480 if (ResTy.isInteger()) {
2481 SDValue Op1 = Op->getOperand(1);
2482 EVT EltTy = VecTy.getVectorElementType();
2483 return DAG.getNode(MipsISD::VEXTRACT_SEXT_ELT, DL, ResTy, Op0, Op1,
2484 DAG.getValueType(EltTy));
2485 }
2486
2487 return Op;
2488}

2490static bool isConstantOrUndef(const SDValue Op) {
2491 if (Op->isUndef())
2492 return true;
2493 if (isa<ConstantSDNode>(Op))
2494 return true;
2495 if (isa<ConstantFPSDNode>(Op))
2496 return true;
2497 return false;
2498}
2499
2500static bool isConstantOrUndefBUILD_VECTOR(const BuildVectorSDNode *Op) {
2501 for (unsigned i = 0; i < Op->getNumOperands(); ++i)
2502 if (isConstantOrUndef(Op->getOperand(i)))
2503 return true;
2504 return false;
2505}
2506
2507// Lowers ISD::BUILD_VECTOR into appropriate SelectionDAG nodes for the
2508// backend.
2509//
2510// Lowers according to the following rules:
2511// - Constant splats are legal as-is as long as the SplatBitSize is a power of
2512// 2 less than or equal to 64 and the value fits into a signed 10-bit
2513// immediate
2514// - Constant splats are lowered to bitconverted BUILD_VECTORs if SplatBitSize
2515// is a power of 2 less than or equal to 64 and the value does not fit into a
2516// signed 10-bit immediate
2517// - Non-constant splats are legal as-is.
2518// - Non-constant non-splats are lowered to sequences of INSERT_VECTOR_ELT.
2519// - All others are illegal and must be expanded.
2520SDValue MipsSETargetLowering::lowerBUILD_VECTOR(SDValue Op,
2521 SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
2522 BuildVectorSDNode *Node = cast<BuildVectorSDNode>(Op);
2523 EVT ResTy = Op->getValueType(0);
2524 SDLoc DL(Op);
2525 APInt SplatValue, SplatUndef;
2526 unsigned SplatBitSize;
2527 bool HasAnyUndefs;
2528
2529 if (!Subtarget.hasMSA() || !ResTy.is128BitVector())
2530 return SDValue();
2531
2532 if (Node->isConstantSplat(SplatValue, SplatUndef, SplatBitSize,
2533 HasAnyUndefs, 8,
2534 !Subtarget.isLittle()) && SplatBitSize <= 64) {
2535 // We can only cope with 8, 16, 32, or 64-bit elements
2536 if (SplatBitSize != 8 && SplatBitSize != 16 && SplatBitSize != 32 &&
2537 SplatBitSize != 64)
2538 return SDValue();
2539
2540 // If the value isn't an integer type we will have to bitcast
2541 // from an integer type first. Also, if there are any undefs, we must
2542 // lower them to defined values first.
2543 if (ResTy.isInteger() && !HasAnyUndefs)
2544 return Op;
2545
2546 EVT ViaVecTy;
2547
2548 switch (SplatBitSize) {
2549 default:
2550 return SDValue();
2551 case 8:
2552 ViaVecTy = MVT::v16i8;
2553 break;
2554 case 16:
2555 ViaVecTy = MVT::v8i16;
2556 break;
2557 case 32:
2558 ViaVecTy = MVT::v4i32;
2559 break;
2560 case 64:
2561 // There's no fill.d to fall back on for 64-bit values
2562 return SDValue();
2563 }
2564
2565 // SelectionDAG::getConstant will promote SplatValue appropriately.
2566 SDValue Result = DAG.getConstant(SplatValue, DL, ViaVecTy);
2567
2568 // Bitcast to the type we originally wanted
2569 if (ViaVecTy != ResTy)
2570 Result = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, SDLoc(Node), ResTy, Result);
2571
2572 return Result;
2573 } else if (DAG.isSplatValue(Op, /* AllowUndefs */ false))
2574 return Op;
2575 else if (!isConstantOrUndefBUILD_VECTOR(Node)) {
2576 // Use INSERT_VECTOR_ELT operations rather than expand to stores.
2577 // The resulting code is the same length as the expansion, but it doesn't
2578 // use memory operations
2579 EVT ResTy = Node->getValueType(0);
2580
2581 assert(ResTy.isVector());
2582
2583 unsigned NumElts = ResTy.getVectorNumElements();
2584 SDValue Vector = DAG.getUNDEF(ResTy);
2585 for (unsigned i = 0; i < NumElts; ++i) {
2586 Vector = DAG.getNode(ISD::INSERT_VECTOR_ELT, DL, ResTy, Vector,
2587 Node->getOperand(i),
2588 DAG.getConstant(i, DL, MVT::i32));
2589 }
2590 return Vector;
2591 }
2592
2593 return SDValue();
2594}
2595
2596// Lower VECTOR_SHUFFLE into SHF (if possible).
2597//
2598// SHF splits the vector into blocks of four elements, then shuffles these
2599// elements according to a <4 x i2> constant (encoded as an integer immediate).
2600//
2601// It is therefore possible to lower into SHF when the mask takes the form:
2602// <a, b, c, d, a+4, b+4, c+4, d+4, a+8, b+8, c+8, d+8, ...>
2603// When undef's appear they are treated as if they were whatever value is
2604// necessary in order to fit the above forms.
2605//
2606// For example:
2607// %2 = shufflevector <8 x i16> %0, <8 x i16> undef,
2608// <8 x i32> <i32 3, i32 2, i32 1, i32 0,
2609// i32 7, i32 6, i32 5, i32 4>
2610// is lowered to:
2611// (SHF_H $w0, $w1, 27)
2612// where the 27 comes from:
2613// 3 + (2 << 2) + (1 << 4) + (0 << 6)
2614static SDValue lowerVECTOR_SHUFFLE_SHF(SDValue Op, EVT ResTy,
2615 SmallVector<int, 16> Indices,
2616 SelectionDAG &DAG) {
2617 int SHFIndices[4] = { -1, -1, -1, -1 };
2618
2619 if (Indices.size() < 4)
2620 return SDValue();
2621
2622 for (unsigned i = 0; i < 4; ++i) {
2623 for (unsigned j = i; j < Indices.size(); j += 4) {
2624 int Idx = Indices[j];
2625
2626 // Convert from vector index to 4-element subvector index
2627 // If an index refers to an element outside of the subvector then give up
2628 if (Idx != -1) {
2629 Idx -= 4 * (j / 4);
2630 if (Idx < 0 || Idx >= 4)
2631 return SDValue();
2632 }
2633
2634 // If the mask has an undef, replace it with the current index.
2635 // Note that it might still be undef if the current index is also undef
2636 if (SHFIndices[i] == -1)
2637 SHFIndices[i] = Idx;
2638
2639 // Check that non-undef values are the same as in the mask. If they
2640 // aren't then give up
2641 if (!(Idx == -1 || Idx == SHFIndices[i]))
2642 return SDValue();
2643 }
2644 }
2645
2646 // Calculate the immediate. Replace any remaining undefs with zero
2647 APInt Imm(32, 0);
2648 for (int i = 3; i >= 0; --i) {
2649 int Idx = SHFIndices[i];
2650
2651 if (Idx == -1)
2652 Idx = 0;
2653
2654 Imm <<= 2;
2655 Imm |= Idx & 0x3;
2656 }
2657
2658 SDLoc DL(Op);
2659 return DAG.getNode(MipsISD::SHF, DL, ResTy,
2660 DAG.getConstant(Imm, DL, MVT::i32), Op->getOperand(0));
2661}

2663/// Determine whether a range fits a regular pattern of values.
2664/// This function accounts for the possibility of jumping over the End iterator.
2665template <typename ValType>
2666static bool
2667fitsRegularPattern(typename SmallVectorImpl<ValType>::const_iterator Begin,
2668 unsigned CheckStride,
2669 typename SmallVectorImpl<ValType>::const_iterator End,
2670 ValType ExpectedIndex, unsigned ExpectedIndexStride) {
2671 auto &I = Begin;
2672
2673 while (I != End) {
2674 if (*I != -1 && *I != ExpectedIndex)
2675 return false;
2676 ExpectedIndex += ExpectedIndexStride;
2677
2678 // Incrementing past End is undefined behaviour so we must increment one
2679 // step at a time and check for End at each step.
2680 for (unsigned n = 0; n < CheckStride && I != End; ++n, ++I)
2681 ; // Empty loop body.
2682 }
2683 return true;
2684}
2685
2686// Determine whether VECTOR_SHUFFLE is a SPLATI.
2687//
2688// It is a SPLATI when the mask is:
2689// <x, x, x, ...>
2690// where x is any valid index.
2691//
2692// When undef's appear in the mask they are treated as if they were whatever
2693// value is necessary in order to fit the above form.
2694static bool isVECTOR_SHUFFLE_SPLATI(SDValue Op, EVT ResTy,
2695 SmallVector<int, 16> Indices,
2696 SelectionDAG &DAG) {
2697 assert((Indices.size() % 2) == 0);
2698
2699 int SplatIndex = -1;
2700 for (const auto &V : Indices) {
2701 if (V != -1) {
2702 SplatIndex = V;
2703 break;
2704 }
2705 }
2706
2707 return fitsRegularPattern<int>(Indices.begin(), 1, Indices.end(), SplatIndex,
2708 0);
2709}

2711// Lower VECTOR_SHUFFLE into ILVEV (if possible).
2712//
2713// ILVEV interleaves the even elements from each vector.
2714//
2715// It is possible to lower into ILVEV when the mask consists of two of the
2716// following forms interleaved:
2717// <0, 2, 4, ...>
2718// <n, n+2, n+4, ...>
2719// where n is the number of elements in the vector.
2720// For example:
2721// <0, 0, 2, 2, 4, 4, ...>
2722// <0, n, 2, n+2, 4, n+4, ...>
2723//
2724// When undef's appear in the mask they are treated as if they were whatever
2725// value is necessary in order to fit the above forms.
2726static SDValue lowerVECTOR_SHUFFLE_ILVEV(SDValue Op, EVT ResTy,
2727 SmallVector<int, 16> Indices,
2728 SelectionDAG &DAG) {
2729 assert((Indices.size() % 2) == 0);
2730
2731 SDValue Wt;
2732 SDValue Ws;
2733 const auto &Begin = Indices.begin();
2734 const auto &End = Indices.end();
2735
2736 // Check even elements are taken from the even elements of one half or the
2737 // other and pick an operand accordingly.
2738 if (fitsRegularPattern<int>(Begin, 2, End, 0, 2))
2739 Wt = Op->getOperand(0);
2740 else if (fitsRegularPattern<int>(Begin, 2, End, Indices.size(), 2))
2741 Wt = Op->getOperand(1);
2742 else
2743 return SDValue();
2744
2745 // Check odd elements are taken from the even elements of one half or the
2746 // other and pick an operand accordingly.
2747 if (fitsRegularPattern<int>(Begin + 1, 2, End, 0, 2))
2748 Ws = Op->getOperand(0);
2749 else if (fitsRegularPattern<int>(Begin + 1, 2, End, Indices.size(), 2))
2750 Ws = Op->getOperand(1);
2751 else
2752 return SDValue();
2753
2754 return DAG.getNode(MipsISD::ILVEV, SDLoc(Op), ResTy, Ws, Wt);
2755}

2765// where n is the number of elements in the vector.
2766// For example:

2768// <1, n+1, 3, n+3, 5, n+5, ...>

2770// When undef's appear in the mask they are treated as if they were whatever

2780 const auto &End = Indices.end();
2781
2782 // Check even elements are taken from the odd elements of one half or the

2787 Wt = Op->getOperand(1);

2795 else if (fitsRegularPattern<int>(Begin + 1, 2, End, Indices.size() + 1, 2))
2796 Ws = Op->getOperand(1);

2798 return SDValue();

2833 else if (fitsRegularPattern<int>(Begin, 2, End, Indices.size(), 1))
2834 Wt = Op->getOperand(1);

2842 else if (fitsRegularPattern<int>(Begin + 1, 2, End, Indices.size(), 1))

2850// Lower VECTOR_SHUFFLE into ILVL (if possible).
2851//
2852// ILVL interleaves consecutive elements from the left (highest-indexed) half
2853// of each vector.
2854//
2855// It is possible to lower into ILVL when the mask consists of two of the
2856// following forms interleaved:
2857// <x, x+1, x+2, ...>
2858// <n+x, n+x+1, n+x+2, ...>
2859// where n is the number of elements in the vector and x is half n.
2860// For example:
2861// <x, x, x+1, x+1, x+2, x+2, ...>
2862// <x, n+x, x+1, n+x+1, x+2, n+x+2, ...>
2863//
2864// When undef's appear in the mask they are treated as if they were whatever
2865// value is necessary in order to fit the above forms.
2866static SDValue lowerVECTOR_SHUFFLE_ILVL(SDValue Op, EVT ResTy,
2867 SmallVector<int, 16> Indices,
2868 SelectionDAG &DAG) {
2869 assert((Indices.size() % 2) == 0);
2870
2871 unsigned HalfSize = Indices.size() / 2;
2872 SDValue Wt;
2873 SDValue Ws;
2874 const auto &Begin = Indices.begin();
2875 const auto &End = Indices.end();
2876
2877 // Check even elements are taken from the left (highest-indexed) elements of
2878 // one half or the other and pick an operand accordingly.
2879 if (fitsRegularPattern<int>(Begin, 2, End, HalfSize, 1))
2880 Wt = Op->getOperand(0);
2881 else if (fitsRegularPattern<int>(Begin, 2, End, Indices.size() + HalfSize, 1))
2882 Wt = Op->getOperand(1);
2883 else
2884 return SDValue();
2885
2886 // Check odd elements are taken from the left (highest-indexed) elements of
2887 // one half or the other and pick an operand accordingly.
2888 if (fitsRegularPattern<int>(Begin + 1, 2, End, HalfSize, 1))
2889 Ws = Op->getOperand(0);
2890 else if (fitsRegularPattern<int>(Begin + 1, 2, End, Indices.size() + HalfSize,
2891 1))
2892 Ws = Op->getOperand(1);
2893 else
2894 return SDValue();
2895
2896 return DAG.getNode(MipsISD::ILVL, SDLoc(Op), ResTy, Ws, Wt);
2897}

2899// Lower VECTOR_SHUFFLE into PCKEV (if possible).
2900//
2901// PCKEV copies the even elements of each vector into the result vector.
2902//
2903// It is possible to lower into PCKEV when the mask consists of two of the
2904// following forms concatenated:
2905// <0, 2, 4, ...>
2906// <n, n+2, n+4, ...>
2907// where n is the number of elements in the vector.
2908// For example:
2909// <0, 2, 4, ..., 0, 2, 4, ...>
2910// <0, 2, 4, ..., n, n+2, n+4, ...>

2923 const auto &End = Indices.end();

2926 Wt = Op->getOperand(0);

2928 Wt = Op->getOperand(1);

2932 if (fitsRegularPattern<int>(Mid, 1, End, 0, 2))
2933 Ws = Op->getOperand(0);

2935 Ws = Op->getOperand(1);

2976 Ws = Op->getOperand(0);
2977 else if (fitsRegularPattern<int>(Mid, 1, End, Indices.size() + 1, 2))

2985// Lower VECTOR_SHUFFLE into VSHF.
2986//
2987// This mostly consists of converting the shuffle indices in Indices into a
2988// BUILD_VECTOR and adding it as an operand to the resulting VSHF. There is
2989// also code to eliminate unused operands of the VECTOR_SHUFFLE. For example,
2990// if the type is v8i16 and all the indices are less than 8 then the second
2991// operand is unused and can be replaced with anything. We choose to replace it
2992// with the used operand since this reduces the number of instructions overall.
2993static SDValue lowerVECTOR_SHUFFLE_VSHF(SDValue Op, EVT ResTy,
2994 SmallVector<int, 16> Indices,
2995 SelectionDAG &DAG) {
2996 SmallVector<SDValue, 16> Ops;
2997 SDValue Op0;
2998 SDValue Op1;
2999 EVT MaskVecTy = ResTy.changeVectorElementTypeToInteger();
3000 EVT MaskEltTy = MaskVecTy.getVectorElementType();
3001 bool Using1stVec = false;
3002 bool Using2ndVec = false;
3003 SDLoc DL(Op);
3004 int ResTyNumElts = ResTy.getVectorNumElements();
3005
3006 for (int i = 0; i < ResTyNumElts; ++i) {
3007 // Idx == -1 means UNDEF
3008 int Idx = Indices[i];
3009
3010 if (0 <= Idx && Idx < ResTyNumElts)
3011 Using1stVec = true;
3012 if (ResTyNumElts <= Idx && Idx < ResTyNumElts * 2)
3013 Using2ndVec = true;
3014 }
3015
3016 for (SmallVector<int, 16>::iterator I = Indices.begin(); I != Indices.end();
3017 ++I)
3018 Ops.push_back(DAG.getTargetConstant(*I, DL, MaskEltTy));
3019
3020 SDValue MaskVec = DAG.getBuildVector(MaskVecTy, DL, Ops);
3021
3022 if (Using1stVec && Using2ndVec) {
3023 Op0 = Op->getOperand(0);
3024 Op1 = Op->getOperand(1);
3025 } else if (Using1stVec)
3026 Op0 = Op1 = Op->getOperand(0);
3027 else if (Using2ndVec)
3028 Op0 = Op1 = Op->getOperand(1);
3029 else
3030 llvm_unreachable("shuffle vector mask references neither vector operand?");
3031
3032 // VECTOR_SHUFFLE concatenates the vectors in an vectorwise fashion.
3033 // <0b00, 0b01> + <0b10, 0b11> -> <0b00, 0b01, 0b10, 0b11>
3034 // VSHF concatenates the vectors in a bitwise fashion:
3035 // <0b00, 0b01> + <0b10, 0b11> ->
3036 // 0b0100 + 0b1110 -> 0b01001110
3037 // <0b10, 0b11, 0b00, 0b01>
3038 // We must therefore swap the operands to get the correct result.
3039 return DAG.getNode(MipsISD::VSHF, DL, ResTy, MaskVec, Op1, Op0);
3040}
3041
3042// Lower VECTOR_SHUFFLE into one of a number of instructions depending on the
3043// indices in the shuffle.
3044SDValue MipsSETargetLowering::lowerVECTOR_SHUFFLE(SDValue Op,
3045 SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
3046 ShuffleVectorSDNode *Node = cast<ShuffleVectorSDNode>(Op);
3047 EVT ResTy = Op->getValueType(0);
3048
3049 if (!ResTy.is128BitVector())
3050 return SDValue();
3051
3052 int ResTyNumElts = ResTy.getVectorNumElements();
3053 SmallVector<int, 16> Indices;
3054
3055 for (int i = 0; i < ResTyNumElts; ++i)
3056 Indices.push_back(Node->getMaskElt(i));
3057
3058 // splati.[bhwd] is preferable to the others but is matched from
3059 // MipsISD::VSHF.
3060 if (isVECTOR_SHUFFLE_SPLATI(Op, ResTy, Indices, DAG))
3061 return lowerVECTOR_SHUFFLE_VSHF(Op, ResTy, Indices, DAG);
3062 SDValue Result;
3063 if ((Result = lowerVECTOR_SHUFFLE_ILVEV(Op, ResTy, Indices, DAG)))
3064 return Result;
3065 if ((Result = lowerVECTOR_SHUFFLE_ILVOD(Op, ResTy, Indices, DAG)))
3066 return Result;
3067 if ((Result = lowerVECTOR_SHUFFLE_ILVL(Op, ResTy, Indices, DAG)))
3068 return Result;
3069 if ((Result = lowerVECTOR_SHUFFLE_ILVR(Op, ResTy, Indices, DAG)))
3070 return Result;
3071 if ((Result = lowerVECTOR_SHUFFLE_PCKEV(Op, ResTy, Indices, DAG)))
3072 return Result;
3073 if ((Result = lowerVECTOR_SHUFFLE_PCKOD(Op, ResTy, Indices, DAG)))
3074 return Result;
3075 if ((Result = lowerVECTOR_SHUFFLE_SHF(Op, ResTy, Indices, DAG)))
3076 return Result;
3077 return lowerVECTOR_SHUFFLE_VSHF(Op, ResTy, Indices, DAG);
3078}
3079
3080MachineBasicBlock *
3081MipsSETargetLowering::emitBPOSGE32(MachineInstr &MI,
3082 MachineBasicBlock *BB) const {
3083 // $bb:
3084 // bposge32_pseudo $vr0
3085 // =>
3086 // $bb:
3087 // bposge32 $tbb
3088 // $fbb:
3089 // li $vr2, 0
3090 // b $sink
3091 // $tbb:
3092 // li $vr1, 1
3093 // $sink:
3094 // $vr0 = phi($vr2, $fbb, $vr1, $tbb)
3095
3096 MachineRegisterInfo &RegInfo = BB->getParent()->getRegInfo();
3097 const TargetInstrInfo *TII = Subtarget.getInstrInfo();
3098 const TargetRegisterClass *RC = &Mips::GPR32RegClass;
3099 DebugLoc DL = MI.getDebugLoc();
3100 const BasicBlock *LLVM_BB = BB->getBasicBlock();
3101 MachineFunction::iterator It = std::next(MachineFunction::iterator(BB));
3102 MachineFunction *F = BB->getParent();
3103 MachineBasicBlock *FBB = F->CreateMachineBasicBlock(LLVM_BB);
3104 MachineBasicBlock *TBB = F->CreateMachineBasicBlock(LLVM_BB);
3105 MachineBasicBlock *Sink = F->CreateMachineBasicBlock(LLVM_BB);
3106 F->insert(It, FBB);
3107 F->insert(It, TBB);
3108 F->insert(It, Sink);
3109
3110 // Transfer the remainder of BB and its successor edges to Sink.
3111 Sink->splice(Sink->begin(), BB, std::next(MachineBasicBlock::iterator(MI)),
3112 BB->end());
3113 Sink->transferSuccessorsAndUpdatePHIs(BB);
3114
3115 // Add successors.
3116 BB->addSuccessor(FBB);
3117 BB->addSuccessor(TBB);
3118 FBB->addSuccessor(Sink);
3119 TBB->addSuccessor(Sink);
3120
3121 // Insert the real bposge32 instruction to $BB.
3122 BuildMI(BB, DL, TII->get(Mips::BPOSGE32)).addMBB(TBB);
3123 // Insert the real bposge32c instruction to $BB.
3124 BuildMI(BB, DL, TII->get(Mips::BPOSGE32C_MMR3)).addMBB(TBB);
3125
3126 // Fill $FBB.
3127 unsigned VR2 = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(RC);
3128 BuildMI(*FBB, FBB->end(), DL, TII->get(Mips::ADDiu), VR2)
3129 .addReg(Mips::ZERO).addImm(0);
3130 BuildMI(*FBB, FBB->end(), DL, TII->get(Mips::B)).addMBB(Sink);
3131
3132 // Fill $TBB.
3133 unsigned VR1 = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(RC);
3134 BuildMI(*TBB, TBB->end(), DL, TII->get(Mips::ADDiu), VR1)
3135 .addReg(Mips::ZERO).addImm(1);
3136
3137 // Insert phi function to $Sink.
3138 BuildMI(*Sink, Sink->begin(), DL, TII->get(Mips::PHI),
3139 MI.getOperand(0).getReg())
3140 .addReg(VR2)
3141 .addMBB(FBB)
3142 .addReg(VR1)
3143 .addMBB(TBB);
3144
3145 MI.eraseFromParent(); // The pseudo instruction is gone now.
3146 return Sink;
3147}
3148
3149MachineBasicBlock *MipsSETargetLowering::emitMSACBranchPseudo(
3150 MachineInstr &MI, MachineBasicBlock *BB, unsigned BranchOp) const {
3151 // $bb:
3152 // vany_nonzero $rd, $ws
3153 // =>
3154 // $bb:
3155 // bnz.b $ws, $tbb
3156 // b $fbb
3157 // $fbb:
3158 // li $rd1, 0
3159 // b $sink
3160 // $tbb:
3161 // li $rd2, 1
3162 // $sink:
3163 // $rd = phi($rd1, $fbb, $rd2, $tbb)
3164
3165 MachineRegisterInfo &RegInfo = BB->getParent()->getRegInfo();
3166 const TargetInstrInfo *TII = Subtarget.getInstrInfo();
3167 const TargetRegisterClass *RC = &Mips::GPR32RegClass;
3168 DebugLoc DL = MI.getDebugLoc();
3169 const BasicBlock *LLVM_BB = BB->getBasicBlock();
3170 MachineFunction::iterator It = std::next(MachineFunction::iterator(BB));
3171 MachineFunction *F = BB->getParent();
3172 MachineBasicBlock *FBB = F->CreateMachineBasicBlock(LLVM_BB);
3173 MachineBasicBlock *TBB = F->CreateMachineBasicBlock(LLVM_BB);
3174 MachineBasicBlock *Sink = F->CreateMachineBasicBlock(LLVM_BB);
3175 F->insert(It, FBB);
3176 F->insert(It, TBB);
3177 F->insert(It, Sink);
3178
3179 // Transfer the remainder of BB and its successor edges to Sink.
3180 Sink->splice(Sink->begin(), BB, std::next(MachineBasicBlock::iterator(MI)),
3181 BB->end());
3182 Sink->transferSuccessorsAndUpdatePHIs(BB);
3183
3184 // Add successors.
3185 BB->addSuccessor(FBB);
3186 BB->addSuccessor(TBB);
3187 FBB->addSuccessor(Sink);
3188 TBB->addSuccessor(Sink);
3189
3190 // Insert the real bnz.b instruction to $BB.
3191 BuildMI(BB, DL, TII->get(BranchOp))
3192 .addReg(MI.getOperand(1).getReg())
3193 .addMBB(TBB);
3194
3195 // Fill $FBB.
3196 unsigned RD1 = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(RC);
3197 BuildMI(*FBB, FBB->end(), DL, TII->get(Mips::ADDiu), RD1)
3198 .addReg(Mips::ZERO).addImm(0);
3199 BuildMI(*FBB, FBB->end(), DL, TII->get(Mips::B)).addMBB(Sink);
3200
3201 // Fill $TBB.
3202 unsigned RD2 = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(RC);
3203 BuildMI(*TBB, TBB->end(), DL, TII->get(Mips::ADDiu), RD2)
3204 .addReg(Mips::ZERO).addImm(1);
3205
3206 // Insert phi function to $Sink.
3207 BuildMI(*Sink, Sink->begin(), DL, TII->get(Mips::PHI),
3208 MI.getOperand(0).getReg())
3209 .addReg(RD1)
3210 .addMBB(FBB)
3211 .addReg(RD2)
3212 .addMBB(TBB);
3213
3214 MI.eraseFromParent(); // The pseudo instruction is gone now.
3215 return Sink;
3216}

3218// Emit the COPY_FW pseudo instruction.
3219//
3220// copy_fw_pseudo $fd, $ws, n
3221// =>
3222// copy_u_w $rt, $ws, $n
3223// mtc1 $rt, $fd
3224//
3225// When n is zero, the equivalent operation can be performed with (potentially)
3226// zero instructions due to register overlaps. This optimization is never valid
3227// for lane 1 because it would require FR=0 mode which isn't supported by MSA.
3228MachineBasicBlock *
3229MipsSETargetLowering::emitCOPY_FW(MachineInstr &MI,
3230 MachineBasicBlock *BB) const {
3231 const TargetInstrInfo *TII = Subtarget.getInstrInfo();
3232 MachineRegisterInfo &RegInfo = BB->getParent()->getRegInfo();
3233 DebugLoc DL = MI.getDebugLoc();
3234 unsigned Fd = MI.getOperand(0).getReg();
3235 unsigned Ws = MI.getOperand(1).getReg();
3236 unsigned Lane = MI.getOperand(2).getImm();
3237
3238 if (Lane == 0) {
3239 unsigned Wt = Ws;
3240 if (!Subtarget.useOddSPReg()) {
3241 // We must copy to an even-numbered MSA register so that the
3242 // single-precision sub-register is also guaranteed to be even-numbered.
3243 Wt = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(&Mips::MSA128WEvensRegClass);
3244
3245 BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII->get(Mips::COPY), Wt).addReg(Ws);
3246 }
3247
3248 BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII->get(Mips::COPY), Fd).addReg(Wt, 0, Mips::sub_lo);
3249 } else {
3250 unsigned Wt = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(
3251 Subtarget.useOddSPReg() ? &Mips::MSA128WRegClass :
3252 &Mips::MSA128WEvensRegClass);
3253
3254 BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII->get(Mips::SPLATI_W), Wt).addReg(Ws).addImm(Lane);
3255 BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII->get(Mips::COPY), Fd).addReg(Wt, 0, Mips::sub_lo);
3256 }
3257
3258 MI.eraseFromParent(); // The pseudo instruction is gone now.
3259 return BB;
3260}

3262// Emit the COPY_FD pseudo instruction.
3263//
3264// copy_fd_pseudo $fd, $ws, n
3265// =>
3266// splati.d $wt, $ws, $n
3267// copy $fd, $wt:sub_64
3268//
3269// When n is zero, the equivalent operation can be performed with (potentially)
3270// zero instructions due to register overlaps. This optimization is always
3271// valid because FR=1 mode which is the only supported mode in MSA.
3272MachineBasicBlock *
3273MipsSETargetLowering::emitCOPY_FD(MachineInstr &MI,
3274 MachineBasicBlock *BB) const {
3275 assert(Subtarget.isFP64bit());
3276
3277 const TargetInstrInfo *TII = Subtarget.getInstrInfo();
3278 MachineRegisterInfo &RegInfo = BB->getParent()->getRegInfo();
3279 unsigned Fd = MI.getOperand(0).getReg();
3280 unsigned Ws = MI.getOperand(1).getReg();
3281 unsigned Lane = MI.getOperand(2).getImm() * 2;
3282 DebugLoc DL = MI.getDebugLoc();
3283
3284 if (Lane == 0)
3285 BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII->get(Mips::COPY), Fd).addReg(Ws, 0, Mips::sub_64);
3286 else {
3287 unsigned Wt = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(&Mips::MSA128DRegClass);
3288
3289 BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII->get(Mips::SPLATI_D), Wt).addReg(Ws).addImm(1);
3290 BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII->get(Mips::COPY), Fd).addReg(Wt, 0, Mips::sub_64);
3291 }
3292
3293 MI.eraseFromParent(); // The pseudo instruction is gone now.
3294 return BB;
3295}
