3365// Emit the INSERT_([BHWD]|F[WD])_VIDX pseudo instruction.
3366//
3367// For integer:
3368// (INSERT_([BHWD]|F[WD])_PSEUDO $wd, $wd_in, $n, $rs)
3369// =>
3370// (SLL $lanetmp1, $lane, <log2size)
3371// (SLD_B $wdtmp1, $wd_in, $wd_in, $lanetmp1)
3372// (INSERT_[BHWD], $wdtmp2, $wdtmp1, 0, $rs)
3373// (NEG $lanetmp2, $lanetmp1)
3374// (SLD_B $wd, $wdtmp2, $wdtmp2, $lanetmp2)
3375//
3376// For floating point:
3377// (INSERT_([BHWD]|F[WD])_PSEUDO $wd, $wd_in, $n, $fs)
3378// =>
3379// (SUBREG_TO_REG $wt, $fs, <subreg>)
3380// (SLL $lanetmp1, $lane, <log2size)
3381// (SLD_B $wdtmp1, $wd_in, $wd_in, $lanetmp1)
3382// (INSVE_[WD], $wdtmp2, 0, $wdtmp1, 0)
3383// (NEG $lanetmp2, $lanetmp1)
3384// (SLD_B $wd, $wdtmp2, $wdtmp2, $lanetmp2)
3385MachineBasicBlock *MipsSETargetLowering::emitINSERT_DF_VIDX(
3386 MachineInstr &MI, MachineBasicBlock *BB, unsigned EltSizeInBytes,
3387 bool IsFP) const {
3388 const TargetInstrInfo *TII = Subtarget.getInstrInfo();
3389 MachineRegisterInfo &RegInfo = BB->getParent()->getRegInfo();
3390 DebugLoc DL = MI.getDebugLoc();
3391 unsigned Wd = MI.getOperand(0).getReg();
3392 unsigned SrcVecReg = MI.getOperand(1).getReg();
3393 unsigned LaneReg = MI.getOperand(2).getReg();
3394 unsigned SrcValReg = MI.getOperand(3).getReg();
3395
3396 const TargetRegisterClass *VecRC = nullptr;
3397 // FIXME: This should be true for N32 too.
3398 const TargetRegisterClass *GPRRC =
3399 Subtarget.isABI_N64() ? &Mips::GPR64RegClass : &Mips::GPR32RegClass;
3400 unsigned SubRegIdx = Subtarget.isABI_N64() ? Mips::sub_32 : 0;
3401 unsigned ShiftOp = Subtarget.isABI_N64() ? Mips::DSLL : Mips::SLL;
3402 unsigned EltLog2Size;
3403 unsigned InsertOp = 0;
3404 unsigned InsveOp = 0;
3405 switch (EltSizeInBytes) {
3406 default:
3407 llvm_unreachable("Unexpected size");
3408 case 1:
3409 EltLog2Size = 0;
3410 InsertOp = Mips::INSERT_B;
3411 InsveOp = Mips::INSVE_B;
3412 VecRC = &Mips::MSA128BRegClass;
3413 break;
3414 case 2:
3415 EltLog2Size = 1;
3416 InsertOp = Mips::INSERT_H;
3417 InsveOp = Mips::INSVE_H;
3418 VecRC = &Mips::MSA128HRegClass;
3419 break;
3420 case 4:
3421 EltLog2Size = 2;
3422 InsertOp = Mips::INSERT_W;
3423 InsveOp = Mips::INSVE_W;
3424 VecRC = &Mips::MSA128WRegClass;
3425 break;
3426 case 8:
3427 EltLog2Size = 3;
3428 InsertOp = Mips::INSERT_D;
3429 InsveOp = Mips::INSVE_D;
3430 VecRC = &Mips::MSA128DRegClass;
3431 break;
3432 }
3433
3434 if (IsFP) {
3435 unsigned Wt = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(VecRC);
3436 BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII->get(Mips::SUBREG_TO_REG), Wt)
3437 .addImm(0)
3438 .addReg(SrcValReg)
3439 .addImm(EltSizeInBytes == 8 ? Mips::sub_64 : Mips::sub_lo);
3440 SrcValReg = Wt;
3441 }
3442
3443 // Convert the lane index into a byte index
3444 if (EltSizeInBytes != 1) {
3445 unsigned LaneTmp1 = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(GPRRC);
3446 BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII->get(ShiftOp), LaneTmp1)
3447 .addReg(LaneReg)
3448 .addImm(EltLog2Size);
3449 LaneReg = LaneTmp1;
3450 }
3451
3452 // Rotate bytes around so that the desired lane is element zero
3453 unsigned WdTmp1 = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(VecRC);
3454 BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII->get(Mips::SLD_B), WdTmp1)
3455 .addReg(SrcVecReg)
3456 .addReg(SrcVecReg)
3457 .addReg(LaneReg, 0, SubRegIdx);
3458
3459 unsigned WdTmp2 = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(VecRC);
3460 if (IsFP) {
3461 // Use insve.df to insert to element zero
3462 BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII->get(InsveOp), WdTmp2)
3463 .addReg(WdTmp1)
3464 .addImm(0)
3465 .addReg(SrcValReg)
3466 .addImm(0);
3467 } else {
3468 // Use insert.df to insert to element zero
3469 BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII->get(InsertOp), WdTmp2)
3470 .addReg(WdTmp1)
3471 .addReg(SrcValReg)
3472 .addImm(0);
3473 }
3474
3475 // Rotate elements the rest of the way for a full rotation.
3476 // sld.df inteprets $rt modulo the number of columns so we only need to negate
3477 // the lane index to do this.
3478 unsigned LaneTmp2 = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(GPRRC);
3479 BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII->get(Subtarget.isABI_N64() ? Mips::DSUB : Mips::SUB),
3480 LaneTmp2)
3481 .addReg(Subtarget.isABI_N64() ? Mips::ZERO_64 : Mips::ZERO)
3482 .addReg(LaneReg);
3483 BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII->get(Mips::SLD_B), Wd)
3484 .addReg(WdTmp2)
3485 .addReg(WdTmp2)
3486 .addReg(LaneTmp2, 0, SubRegIdx);
3487
3488 MI.eraseFromParent(); // The pseudo instruction is gone now.
3489 return BB;
3490}

3556// Emit the ST_F16_PSEDUO instruction to store a f16 value from an MSA
3557// register.
3558//
3559// STF16 MSA128F16:$wd, mem_simm10:$addr
3560// =>
3561// copy_u.h $rtemp,$wd[0]
3562// sh $rtemp, $addr
3563//
3564// Safety: We can't use st.h & co as they would over write the memory after
3565// the destination. It would require half floats be allocated 16 bytes(!) of
3566// space.
3567MachineBasicBlock *
3568MipsSETargetLowering::emitST_F16_PSEUDO(MachineInstr &MI,
3569 MachineBasicBlock *BB) const {
3570
3571 const TargetInstrInfo *TII = Subtarget.getInstrInfo();
3572 MachineRegisterInfo &RegInfo = BB->getParent()->getRegInfo();
3573 DebugLoc DL = MI.getDebugLoc();
3574 unsigned Ws = MI.getOperand(0).getReg();
3575 unsigned Rt = MI.getOperand(1).getReg();
3576 const MachineMemOperand &MMO = **MI.memoperands_begin();
3577 unsigned Imm = MMO.getOffset();
3578
3579 // Caution: A load via the GOT can expand to a GPR32 operand, a load via
3580 // spill and reload can expand as a GPR64 operand. Examine the
3581 // operand in detail and default to ABI.
3582 const TargetRegisterClass *RC =
3583 MI.getOperand(1).isReg() ? RegInfo.getRegClass(MI.getOperand(1).getReg())
3584 : (Subtarget.isABI_O32() ? &Mips::GPR32RegClass
3585 : &Mips::GPR64RegClass);
3586 const bool UsingMips32 = RC == &Mips::GPR32RegClass;
3587 unsigned Rs = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(&Mips::GPR32RegClass);
3588
3589 BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII->get(Mips::COPY_U_H), Rs).addReg(Ws).addImm(0);
3590 if(!UsingMips32) {
3591 unsigned Tmp = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(&Mips::GPR64RegClass);
3592 BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII->get(Mips::SUBREG_TO_REG), Tmp)
3593 .addImm(0)
3594 .addReg(Rs)
3595 .addImm(Mips::sub_32);
3596 Rs = Tmp;
3597 }
3598 BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII->get(UsingMips32 ? Mips::SH : Mips::SH64))
3599 .addReg(Rs)
3600 .addReg(Rt)
3601 .addImm(Imm)
3602 .addMemOperand(BB->getParent()->getMachineMemOperand(
3603 &MMO, MMO.getOffset(), MMO.getSize()));
3604
3605 MI.eraseFromParent();
3606 return BB;
3607}

3609// Emit the LD_F16_PSEDUO instruction to load a f16 value into an MSA register.
3610//
3611// LD_F16 MSA128F16:$wd, mem_simm10:$addr
3612// =>
3613// lh $rtemp, $addr
3614// fill.h $wd, $rtemp
3615//
3616// Safety: We can't use ld.h & co as they over-read from the source.
3617// Additionally, if the address is not modulo 16, 2 cases can occur:
3618// a) Segmentation fault as the load instruction reads from a memory page
3619// memory it's not supposed to.
3620// b) The load crosses an implementation specific boundary, requiring OS
3621// intervention.
3622MachineBasicBlock *
3623MipsSETargetLowering::emitLD_F16_PSEUDO(MachineInstr &MI,
3624 MachineBasicBlock *BB) const {
3625
3626 const TargetInstrInfo *TII = Subtarget.getInstrInfo();
3627 MachineRegisterInfo &RegInfo = BB->getParent()->getRegInfo();
3628 DebugLoc DL = MI.getDebugLoc();
3629 unsigned Wd = MI.getOperand(0).getReg();
3630
3631 // Caution: A load via the GOT can expand to a GPR32 operand, a load via
3632 // spill and reload can expand as a GPR64 operand. Examine the
3633 // operand in detail and default to ABI.
3634 const TargetRegisterClass *RC =
3635 MI.getOperand(1).isReg() ? RegInfo.getRegClass(MI.getOperand(1).getReg())
3636 : (Subtarget.isABI_O32() ? &Mips::GPR32RegClass
3637 : &Mips::GPR64RegClass);
3638
3639 const bool UsingMips32 = RC == &Mips::GPR32RegClass;
3640 unsigned Rt = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(RC);
3641
3642 MachineInstrBuilder MIB =
3643 BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII->get(UsingMips32 ? Mips::LH : Mips::LH64), Rt);
3644 for (unsigned i = 1; i < MI.getNumOperands(); i++)
3645 MIB.add(MI.getOperand(i));
3646
3647 if(!UsingMips32) {
3648 unsigned Tmp = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(&Mips::GPR32RegClass);
3649 BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII->get(Mips::COPY), Tmp).addReg(Rt, 0, Mips::sub_32);
3650 Rt = Tmp;
3651 }
3652
3653 BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII->get(Mips::FILL_H), Wd).addReg(Rt);
3654
3655 MI.eraseFromParent();
3656 return BB;
3657}

3659// Emit the FPROUND_PSEUDO instruction.
3660//
3661// Round an FGR64Opnd, FGR32Opnd to an f16.
3662//
3663// Safety: Cycle the operand through the GPRs so the result always ends up
3664// the correct MSA register.
3665//
3666// FIXME: This copying is strictly unnecessary. If we could tie FGR32Opnd:$Fs
3667// / FGR64Opnd:$Fs and MSA128F16:$Wd to the same physical register
3668// (which they can be, as the MSA registers are defined to alias the
3669// FPU's 64 bit and 32 bit registers) the result can be accessed using
3670// the correct register class. That requires operands be tie-able across
3671// register classes which have a sub/super register class relationship.
3672//
3673// For FPG32Opnd:
3674//
3675// FPROUND MSA128F16:$wd, FGR32Opnd:$fs
3676// =>
3677// mfc1 $rtemp, $fs
3678// fill.w $rtemp, $wtemp
3679// fexdo.w $wd, $wtemp, $wtemp
3680//
3681// For FPG64Opnd on mips32r2+:
3682//
3683// FPROUND MSA128F16:$wd, FGR64Opnd:$fs
3684// =>
3685// mfc1 $rtemp, $fs
3686// fill.w $rtemp, $wtemp
3687// mfhc1 $rtemp2, $fs
3688// insert.w $wtemp[1], $rtemp2
3689// insert.w $wtemp[3], $rtemp2
3690// fexdo.w $wtemp2, $wtemp, $wtemp
3691// fexdo.h $wd, $temp2, $temp2
3692//
3693// For FGR64Opnd on mips64r2+:
3694//
3695// FPROUND MSA128F16:$wd, FGR64Opnd:$fs
3696// =>
3697// dmfc1 $rtemp, $fs
3698// fill.d $rtemp, $wtemp
3699// fexdo.w $wtemp2, $wtemp, $wtemp
3700// fexdo.h $wd, $wtemp2, $wtemp2
3701//
3702// Safety note: As $wtemp is UNDEF, we may provoke a spurious exception if the
3703// undef bits are "just right" and the exception enable bits are
3704// set. By using fill.w to replicate $fs into all elements over
3705// insert.w for one element, we avoid that potiential case. If
3706// fexdo.[hw] causes an exception in, the exception is valid and it
3707// occurs for all elements.
3708MachineBasicBlock *
3709MipsSETargetLowering::emitFPROUND_PSEUDO(MachineInstr &MI,
3710 MachineBasicBlock *BB,
3711 bool IsFGR64) const {
3712
3713 // Strictly speaking, we need MIPS32R5 to support MSA. We'll be generous
3714 // here. It's technically doable to support MIPS32 here, but the ISA forbids
3715 // it.
3716 assert(Subtarget.hasMSA() && Subtarget.hasMips32r2());
3717
3718 bool IsFGR64onMips64 = Subtarget.hasMips64() && IsFGR64;
3719 bool IsFGR64onMips32 = !Subtarget.hasMips64() && IsFGR64;
3720
3721 const TargetInstrInfo *TII = Subtarget.getInstrInfo();
3722 DebugLoc DL = MI.getDebugLoc();
3723 unsigned Wd = MI.getOperand(0).getReg();
3724 unsigned Fs = MI.getOperand(1).getReg();
3725
3726 MachineRegisterInfo &RegInfo = BB->getParent()->getRegInfo();
3727 unsigned Wtemp = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(&Mips::MSA128WRegClass);
3728 const TargetRegisterClass *GPRRC =
3729 IsFGR64onMips64 ? &Mips::GPR64RegClass : &Mips::GPR32RegClass;
3730 unsigned MFC1Opc = IsFGR64onMips64
3731 ? Mips::DMFC1
3732 : (IsFGR64onMips32 ? Mips::MFC1_D64 : Mips::MFC1);
3733 unsigned FILLOpc = IsFGR64onMips64 ? Mips::FILL_D : Mips::FILL_W;
3734
3735 // Perform the register class copy as mentioned above.
3736 unsigned Rtemp = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(GPRRC);
3737 BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII->get(MFC1Opc), Rtemp).addReg(Fs);
3738 BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII->get(FILLOpc), Wtemp).addReg(Rtemp);
3739 unsigned WPHI = Wtemp;
3740
3741 if (IsFGR64onMips32) {
3742 unsigned Rtemp2 = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(GPRRC);
3743 BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII->get(Mips::MFHC1_D64), Rtemp2).addReg(Fs);
3744 unsigned Wtemp2 = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(&Mips::MSA128WRegClass);
3745 unsigned Wtemp3 = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(&Mips::MSA128WRegClass);
3746 BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII->get(Mips::INSERT_W), Wtemp2)
3747 .addReg(Wtemp)
3748 .addReg(Rtemp2)
3749 .addImm(1);
3750 BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII->get(Mips::INSERT_W), Wtemp3)
3751 .addReg(Wtemp2)
3752 .addReg(Rtemp2)
3753 .addImm(3);
3754 WPHI = Wtemp3;
3755 }
3756
3757 if (IsFGR64) {
3758 unsigned Wtemp2 = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(&Mips::MSA128WRegClass);
3759 BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII->get(Mips::FEXDO_W), Wtemp2)
3760 .addReg(WPHI)
3761 .addReg(WPHI);
3762 WPHI = Wtemp2;
3763 }
3764
3765 BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII->get(Mips::FEXDO_H), Wd).addReg(WPHI).addReg(WPHI);
3766
3767 MI.eraseFromParent();
3768 return BB;
3769}
3770
3771// Emit the FPEXTEND_PSEUDO instruction.
3772//
3773// Expand an f16 to either a FGR32Opnd or FGR64Opnd.
3774//
3775// Safety: Cycle the result through the GPRs so the result always ends up
3776// the correct floating point register.
3777//
3778// FIXME: This copying is strictly unnecessary. If we could tie FGR32Opnd:$Fd
3779// / FGR64Opnd:$Fd and MSA128F16:$Ws to the same physical register
3780// (which they can be, as the MSA registers are defined to alias the
3781// FPU's 64 bit and 32 bit registers) the result can be accessed using
3782// the correct register class. That requires operands be tie-able across
3783// register classes which have a sub/super register class relationship. I
3784// haven't checked.
3785//
3786// For FGR32Opnd:
3787//
3788// FPEXTEND FGR32Opnd:$fd, MSA128F16:$ws
3789// =>
3790// fexupr.w $wtemp, $ws
3791// copy_s.w $rtemp, $ws[0]
3792// mtc1 $rtemp, $fd
3793//
3794// For FGR64Opnd on Mips64:
3795//
3796// FPEXTEND FGR64Opnd:$fd, MSA128F16:$ws
3797// =>
3798// fexupr.w $wtemp, $ws
3799// fexupr.d $wtemp2, $wtemp
3800// copy_s.d $rtemp, $wtemp2s[0]
3801// dmtc1 $rtemp, $fd
3802//
3803// For FGR64Opnd on Mips32:
3804//
3805// FPEXTEND FGR64Opnd:$fd, MSA128F16:$ws
3806// =>
3807// fexupr.w $wtemp, $ws
3808// fexupr.d $wtemp2, $wtemp
3809// copy_s.w $rtemp, $wtemp2[0]
3810// mtc1 $rtemp, $ftemp
3811// copy_s.w $rtemp2, $wtemp2[1]
3812// $fd = mthc1 $rtemp2, $ftemp
3813MachineBasicBlock *
3814MipsSETargetLowering::emitFPEXTEND_PSEUDO(MachineInstr &MI,
3815 MachineBasicBlock *BB,
3816 bool IsFGR64) const {
3817
3818 // Strictly speaking, we need MIPS32R5 to support MSA. We'll be generous
3819 // here. It's technically doable to support MIPS32 here, but the ISA forbids
3820 // it.
3821 assert(Subtarget.hasMSA() && Subtarget.hasMips32r2());
3822
3823 bool IsFGR64onMips64 = Subtarget.hasMips64() && IsFGR64;
3824 bool IsFGR64onMips32 = !Subtarget.hasMips64() && IsFGR64;
3825
3826 const TargetInstrInfo *TII = Subtarget.getInstrInfo();
3827 DebugLoc DL = MI.getDebugLoc();
3828 unsigned Fd = MI.getOperand(0).getReg();
3829 unsigned Ws = MI.getOperand(1).getReg();
3830
3831 MachineRegisterInfo &RegInfo = BB->getParent()->getRegInfo();
3832 const TargetRegisterClass *GPRRC =
3833 IsFGR64onMips64 ? &Mips::GPR64RegClass : &Mips::GPR32RegClass;
3834 unsigned MTC1Opc = IsFGR64onMips64
3835 ? Mips::DMTC1
3836 : (IsFGR64onMips32 ? Mips::MTC1_D64 : Mips::MTC1);
3837 unsigned COPYOpc = IsFGR64onMips64 ? Mips::COPY_S_D : Mips::COPY_S_W;
3838
3839 unsigned Wtemp = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(&Mips::MSA128WRegClass);
3840 unsigned WPHI = Wtemp;
3841
3842 BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII->get(Mips::FEXUPR_W), Wtemp).addReg(Ws);
3843 if (IsFGR64) {
3844 WPHI = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(&Mips::MSA128DRegClass);
3845 BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII->get(Mips::FEXUPR_D), WPHI).addReg(Wtemp);
3846 }
3847
3848 // Perform the safety regclass copy mentioned above.
3849 unsigned Rtemp = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(GPRRC);
3850 unsigned FPRPHI = IsFGR64onMips32
3851 ? RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(&Mips::FGR64RegClass)
3852 : Fd;
3853 BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII->get(COPYOpc), Rtemp).addReg(WPHI).addImm(0);
3854 BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII->get(MTC1Opc), FPRPHI).addReg(Rtemp);
3855
3856 if (IsFGR64onMips32) {
3857 unsigned Rtemp2 = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(GPRRC);
3858 BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII->get(Mips::COPY_S_W), Rtemp2)
3859 .addReg(WPHI)
3860 .addImm(1);
3861 BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII->get(Mips::MTHC1_D64), Fd)
3862 .addReg(FPRPHI)
3863 .addReg(Rtemp2);
3864 }
3865
3866 MI.eraseFromParent();
3867 return BB;
3868}

3870// Emit the FEXP2_W_1 pseudo instructions.
3871//
3872// fexp2_w_1_pseudo $wd, $wt
3873// =>
3874// ldi.w $ws, 1
3875// fexp2.w $wd, $ws, $wt
3876MachineBasicBlock *
3877MipsSETargetLowering::emitFEXP2_W_1(MachineInstr &MI,
3878 MachineBasicBlock *BB) const {
3879 const TargetInstrInfo *TII = Subtarget.getInstrInfo();
3880 MachineRegisterInfo &RegInfo = BB->getParent()->getRegInfo();
3881 const TargetRegisterClass *RC = &Mips::MSA128WRegClass;
3882 unsigned Ws1 = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(RC);
3883 unsigned Ws2 = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(RC);
3884 DebugLoc DL = MI.getDebugLoc();
3885
3886 // Splat 1.0 into a vector
3887 BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII->get(Mips::LDI_W), Ws1).addImm(1);
3888 BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII->get(Mips::FFINT_U_W), Ws2).addReg(Ws1);
3889
3890 // Emit 1.0 * fexp2(Wt)
3891 BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII->get(Mips::FEXP2_W), MI.getOperand(0).getReg())
3892 .addReg(Ws2)
3893 .addReg(MI.getOperand(1).getReg());
3894
3895 MI.eraseFromParent(); // The pseudo instruction is gone now.
3896 return BB;
3897}

3927template<unsigned MTC1, unsigned CAPLOAD>
3928static MachineBasicBlock *
3929emitCapFloatLoad(const MipsSubtarget &Subtarget,
3930 const llvm::TargetRegisterClass &RC,
3931 MachineInstr &MI,
3932 MachineBasicBlock *BB) {
3933 DebugLoc DL = MI.getDebugLoc();
3934 MachineRegisterInfo &RegInfo = BB->getParent()->getRegInfo();
3935 unsigned IntReg = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(&RC);
3936 const TargetInstrInfo *TII = Subtarget.getInstrInfo();
3937 BuildMI(*BB, &MI, DL, TII->get(CAPLOAD), IntReg)
3938 .add(MI.getOperand(1))
3939 .add(MI.getOperand(2))
3940 .add(MI.getOperand(3));
3941 BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII->get(MTC1))
3942 .add(MI.getOperand(0))
3943 .addReg(IntReg);
3944 MI.eraseFromParent();
3945 return BB;

3959MachineBasicBlock *
3960MipsSETargetLowering::emitCapNotEqual(MachineInstr &MI,
3961 MachineBasicBlock *BB) const {
3962 bool is64 = (MI.getOpcode() == Mips::CNEPseudo);
3963 unsigned Op = Subtarget.useCheriExactEquals()
3964 ? (is64 ? Mips::CNEXEQ : Mips::CNEXEQ32)
3965 : (is64 ? Mips::CNE : Mips::CNE32);
3966 const TargetInstrInfo *TII = Subtarget.getInstrInfo();
3967 BuildMI(*BB, MI, MI.getDebugLoc(), TII->get(Op))
3968 .add(MI.getOperand(0))
3969 .add(MI.getOperand(1))
3970 .add(MI.getOperand(2));
3971 MI.eraseFromParent();
3972 return BB;

3975MipsSETargetLowering::emitCapEqual(MachineInstr &MI,
